2339  if (auto *ScalableSrcTy = dyn_cast<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(SrcTy)) {
2340  if (auto *FixedDstTy = dyn_cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy)) {
2341  // If we are casting a scalable i1 predicate vector to a fixed i8
2342  // vector, bitcast the source and use a vector extract.
2343  if (ScalableSrcTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(1) &&
2344  ScalableSrcTy->getElementCount().isKnownMultipleOf(8) &&
2345  FixedDstTy->getElementType()->isIntegerTy(8)) {
2346  ScalableSrcTy = llvm::ScalableVectorType::get(
2347  FixedDstTy->getElementType(),
2348  ScalableSrcTy->getElementCount().getKnownMinValue() / 8);
2349  Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, ScalableSrcTy);
2350  }
2351  if (ScalableSrcTy->getElementType() == FixedDstTy->getElementType()) {
2352  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(CGF.CGM.Int64Ty);
2353  return Builder.CreateExtractVector(DstTy, Src, Zero, "cast.fixed");
2354  }
2355  }
2356  }
2357 
2358  // Perform VLAT <-> VLST bitcast through memory.
2359  // TODO: since the llvm.experimental.vector.{insert,extract} intrinsics
2360  // require the element types of the vectors to be the same, we
2361  // need to keep this around for bitcasts between VLAT <-> VLST where
2362  // the element types of the vectors are not the same, until we figure
2363  // out a better way of doing these casts.
2364  if ((isa<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy) &&
2365  isa<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(DstTy)) ||
2366  (isa<llvm::ScalableVectorType>(SrcTy) &&
2367  isa<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy))) {
2368  Address Addr = CGF.CreateDefaultAlignTempAlloca(SrcTy, "saved-value");
2369  LValue LV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType());
2370  CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Src, LV);
2371  Addr = Addr.withElementType(CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(DestTy));
2372  LValue DestLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Addr, DestTy);
2373  DestLV.setTBAAInfo(TBAAAccessInfo::getMayAliasInfo());
2374  return EmitLoadOfLValue(DestLV, CE->getExprLoc());
2375  }
2376  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy);
2377  }
2378  case CK_AddressSpaceConversion: {
2379  Expr::EvalResult Result;
2380  if (E->EvaluateAsRValue(Result, CGF.getContext()) &&
2381  Result.Val.isNullPointer()) {
2382  // If E has side effect, it is emitted even if its final result is a
2383  // null pointer. In that case, a DCE pass should be able to
2384  // eliminate the useless instructions emitted during translating E.
2385  if (Result.HasSideEffects)
2386  Visit(E);
2387  return CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(
2388  ConvertType(DestTy)), DestTy);
2389  }
2390  // Since target may map different address spaces in AST to the same address
2391  // space, an address space conversion may end up as a bitcast.
2392  return CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
2393  CGF, Visit(E), E->getType()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace(),
2394  DestTy->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace(), ConvertType(DestTy));
2395  }
2396  case CK_AtomicToNonAtomic:
2397  case CK_NonAtomicToAtomic:
2398  case CK_UserDefinedConversion:
2399  return Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2400 
2401  case CK_NoOp: {
2402  return CE->changesVolatileQualification() ? EmitLoadOfLValue(CE)
2403  : Visit(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2404  }
2405 
2406  case CK_BaseToDerived: {
2407  const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedClassDecl = DestTy->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
2408  assert(DerivedClassDecl && "BaseToDerived arg isn't a C++ object pointer!");
2409 
2410  Address Base = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E);
2411  Address Derived =
2412  CGF.GetAddressOfDerivedClass(Base, DerivedClassDecl,
2413  CE->path_begin(), CE->path_end(),
2414  CGF.ShouldNullCheckClassCastValue(CE));
2415 
2416  // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p11: Behavior is undefined if a downcast is
2417  // performed and the object is not of the derived type.
2418  if (CGF.sanitizePerformTypeCheck())
2419  CGF.EmitTypeCheck(CodeGenFunction::TCK_DowncastPointer, CE->getExprLoc(),
2420  Derived, DestTy->getPointeeType());
2421 
2422  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast))
2423  CGF.EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(DestTy->getPointeeType(), Derived,
2424  /*MayBeNull=*/true,
2425  CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_DerivedCast,
2426  CE->getBeginLoc());
2427 
2428  return CGF.getAsNaturalPointerTo(Derived, CE->getType()->getPointeeType());
2429  }
2430  case CK_UncheckedDerivedToBase:
2431  case CK_DerivedToBase: {
2432  // The EmitPointerWithAlignment path does this fine; just discard
2433  // the alignment.
2434  return CGF.getAsNaturalPointerTo(CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(CE),
2435  CE->getType()->getPointeeType());
2436  }
2437 
2438  case CK_Dynamic: {
2439  Address V = CGF.EmitPointerWithAlignment(E);
2440  const CXXDynamicCastExpr *DCE = cast<CXXDynamicCastExpr>(CE);
2441  return CGF.EmitDynamicCast(V, DCE);
2442  }
2443 
2444  case CK_ArrayToPointerDecay:
2445  return CGF.getAsNaturalPointerTo(CGF.EmitArrayToPointerDecay(E),
2446  CE->getType()->getPointeeType());
2447  case CK_FunctionToPointerDecay:
2448  return EmitLValue(E).getPointer(CGF);
2449 
2450  case CK_NullToPointer:
2451  if (MustVisitNullValue(E))
2452  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2453 
2454  return CGF.CGM.getNullPointer(cast<llvm::PointerType>(ConvertType(DestTy)),
2455  DestTy);
2456 
2457  case CK_NullToMemberPointer: {
2458  if (MustVisitNullValue(E))
2459  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2460 
2461  const MemberPointerType *MPT = CE->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2462  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitNullMemberPointer(MPT);
2463  }
2464 
2465  case CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer:
2466  case CK_BaseToDerivedMemberPointer:
2467  case CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer: {
2468  Value *Src = Visit(E);
2469 
2470  // Note that the AST doesn't distinguish between checked and
2471  // unchecked member pointer conversions, so we always have to
2472  // implement checked conversions here. This is inefficient when
2473  // actual control flow may be required in order to perform the
2474  // check, which it is for data member pointers (but not member
2475  // function pointers on Itanium and ARM).
2476  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerConversion(CGF, CE, Src);
2477  }
2478 
2479  case CK_ARCProduceObject:
2480  return CGF.EmitARCRetainScalarExpr(E);
2481  case CK_ARCConsumeObject:
2482  return CGF.EmitObjCConsumeObject(E->getType(), Visit(E));
2483  case CK_ARCReclaimReturnedObject:
2484  return CGF.EmitARCReclaimReturnedObject(E, /*allowUnsafe*/ Ignored);
2485  case CK_ARCExtendBlockObject:
2486  return CGF.EmitARCExtendBlockObject(E);
2487 
2488  case CK_CopyAndAutoreleaseBlockObject:
2489  return CGF.EmitBlockCopyAndAutorelease(Visit(E), E->getType());
2490 
2491  case CK_FloatingRealToComplex:
2492  case CK_FloatingComplexCast:
2493  case CK_IntegralRealToComplex:
2494  case CK_IntegralComplexCast:
2495  case CK_IntegralComplexToFloatingComplex:
2496  case CK_FloatingComplexToIntegralComplex:
2497  case CK_ConstructorConversion:
2498  case CK_ToUnion:
2499  case CK_HLSLArrayRValue:
2500  llvm_unreachable("scalar cast to non-scalar value");
2501 
2502  case CK_LValueToRValue:
2503  assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(E->getType(), DestTy));
2504  assert(E->isGLValue() && "lvalue-to-rvalue applied to r-value!");
2505  return Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2506 
2507  case CK_IntegralToPointer: {
2508  Value *Src = Visit(const_cast<Expr*>(E));
2509 
2510  // First, convert to the correct width so that we control the kind of
2511  // extension.
2512  auto DestLLVMTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2513  llvm::Type *MiddleTy = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getIntPtrType(DestLLVMTy);
2514  bool InputSigned = E->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
2515  llvm::Value* IntResult =
2516  Builder.CreateIntCast(Src, MiddleTy, InputSigned, "conv");
2517 
2518  auto *IntToPtr = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(IntResult, DestLLVMTy);
2519 
2520  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2521  // Going from integer to pointer that could be dynamic requires reloading
2522  // dynamic information from invariant.group.
2523  if (DestTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
2524  IntToPtr = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(IntToPtr);
2525  }
2526  return IntToPtr;
2527  }
2528  case CK_PointerToIntegral: {
2529  assert(!DestTy->isBooleanType() && "bool should use PointerToBool");
2530  auto *PtrExpr = Visit(E);
2531 
2532  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers) {
2533  const QualType SrcType = E->getType();
2534 
2535  // Casting to integer requires stripping dynamic information as it does
2536  // not carries it.
2537  if (SrcType.mayBeDynamicClass())
2538  PtrExpr = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(PtrExpr);
2539  }
2540 
2541  return Builder.CreatePtrToInt(PtrExpr, ConvertType(DestTy));
2542  }
2543  case CK_ToVoid: {
2544  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E);
2545  return nullptr;
2546  }
2547  case CK_MatrixCast: {
2548  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2549  CE->getExprLoc());
2550  }
2551  case CK_VectorSplat: {
2552  llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(DestTy);
2553  Value *Elt = Visit(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2554  // Splat the element across to all elements
2555  llvm::ElementCount NumElements =
2556  cast<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)->getElementCount();
2557  return Builder.CreateVectorSplat(NumElements, Elt, "splat");
2558  }
2559 
2560  case CK_FixedPointCast:
2561  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2562  CE->getExprLoc());
2563 
2564  case CK_FixedPointToBoolean:
2565  assert(E->getType()->isFixedPointType() &&
2566  "Expected src type to be fixed point type");
2567  assert(DestTy->isBooleanType() && "Expected dest type to be boolean type");
2568  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2569  CE->getExprLoc());
2570 
2571  case CK_FixedPointToIntegral:
2572  assert(E->getType()->isFixedPointType() &&
2573  "Expected src type to be fixed point type");
2574  assert(DestTy->isIntegerType() && "Expected dest type to be an integer");
2575  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2576  CE->getExprLoc());
2577 
2578  case CK_IntegralToFixedPoint:
2579  assert(E->getType()->isIntegerType() &&
2580  "Expected src type to be an integer");
2581  assert(DestTy->isFixedPointType() &&
2582  "Expected dest type to be fixed point type");
2583  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2584  CE->getExprLoc());
2585 
2586  case CK_IntegralCast: {
2587  if (E->getType()->isExtVectorType() && DestTy->isExtVectorType()) {
2588  QualType SrcElTy = E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2589  return Builder.CreateIntCast(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy),
2590  SrcElTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType(),
2591  "conv");
2592  }
2593  ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2594  if (auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE)) {
2595  if (!ICE->isPartOfExplicitCast())
2596  Opts = ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts);
2597  }
2598  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2599  CE->getExprLoc(), Opts);
2600  }
2601  case CK_IntegralToFloating: {
2602  if (E->getType()->isVectorType() && DestTy->isVectorType()) {
2603  // TODO: Support constrained FP intrinsics.
2604  QualType SrcElTy = E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2605  if (SrcElTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType())
2606  return Builder.CreateSIToFP(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy), "conv");
2607  return Builder.CreateUIToFP(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy), "conv");
2608  }
2609  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2610  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2611  CE->getExprLoc());
2612  }
2613  case CK_FloatingToIntegral: {
2614  if (E->getType()->isVectorType() && DestTy->isVectorType()) {
2615  // TODO: Support constrained FP intrinsics.
2616  QualType DstElTy = DestTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2617  if (DstElTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType())
2618  return Builder.CreateFPToSI(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy), "conv");
2619  return Builder.CreateFPToUI(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy), "conv");
2620  }
2621  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2622  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2623  CE->getExprLoc());
2624  }
2625  case CK_FloatingCast: {
2626  if (E->getType()->isVectorType() && DestTy->isVectorType()) {
2627  // TODO: Support constrained FP intrinsics.
2628  QualType SrcElTy = E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2629  QualType DstElTy = DestTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
2630  if (DstElTy->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind() <
2631  SrcElTy->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind())
2632  return Builder.CreateFPTrunc(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy), "conv");
2633  return Builder.CreateFPExt(Visit(E), ConvertType(DestTy), "conv");
2634  }
2635  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2636  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2637  CE->getExprLoc());
2638  }
2639  case CK_FixedPointToFloating:
2640  case CK_FloatingToFixedPoint: {
2641  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2642  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2643  CE->getExprLoc());
2644  }
2645  case CK_BooleanToSignedIntegral: {
2646  ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2647  Opts.TreatBooleanAsSigned = true;
2648  return EmitScalarConversion(Visit(E), E->getType(), DestTy,
2649  CE->getExprLoc(), Opts);
2650  }
2651  case CK_IntegralToBoolean:
2652  return EmitIntToBoolConversion(Visit(E));
2653  case CK_PointerToBoolean:
2654  return EmitPointerToBoolConversion(Visit(E), E->getType());
2655  case CK_FloatingToBoolean: {
2656  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, CE);
2657  return EmitFloatToBoolConversion(Visit(E));
2658  }
2659  case CK_MemberPointerToBoolean: {
2660  llvm::Value *MemPtr = Visit(E);
2661  const MemberPointerType *MPT = E->getType()->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2662  return CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerIsNotNull(CGF, MemPtr, MPT);
2663  }
2664 
2665  case CK_FloatingComplexToReal:
2666  case CK_IntegralComplexToReal:
2667  return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E, false, true).first;
2668 
2669  case CK_FloatingComplexToBoolean:
2670  case CK_IntegralComplexToBoolean: {
2671  CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy V = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E);
2672 
2673  // TODO: kill this function off, inline appropriate case here
2674  return EmitComplexToScalarConversion(V, E->getType(), DestTy,
2675  CE->getExprLoc());
2676  }
2677 
2678  case CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType: {
2679  assert((DestTy->isEventT() || DestTy->isQueueT() ||
2680  DestTy->isOCLIntelSubgroupAVCType()) &&
2681  "CK_ZeroToOCLEvent cast on non-event type");
2682  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(DestTy));
2683  }
2684 
2685  case CK_IntToOCLSampler:
2686  return CGF.CGM.createOpenCLIntToSamplerConversion(E, CGF);
2687 
2688  case CK_HLSLVectorTruncation: {
2689  assert(DestTy->isVectorType() && "Expected dest type to be vector type");
2690  Value *Vec = Visit(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
2691  SmallVector<int, 16> Mask;
2692  unsigned NumElts = DestTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getNumElements();
2693  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumElts; ++I)
2694  Mask.push_back(I);
2695 
2696  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Vec, Mask, "trunc");
2697  }
2698 
2699  } // end of switch
2700 
2701  llvm_unreachable("unknown scalar cast");
2702 }
2703 
2704 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitStmtExpr(const StmtExpr *E) {
2705  CodeGenFunction::StmtExprEvaluation eval(CGF);
2706  Address RetAlloca = CGF.EmitCompoundStmt(*E->getSubStmt(),
2707  !E->getType()->isVoidType());
2708  if (!RetAlloca.isValid())
2709  return nullptr;
2710  return CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(CGF.MakeAddrLValue(RetAlloca, E->getType()),
2711  E->getExprLoc());
2712 }
2713 
2714 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitExprWithCleanups(ExprWithCleanups *E) {
2715  CodeGenFunction::RunCleanupsScope Scope(CGF);
2716  Value *V = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
2717  // Defend against dominance problems caused by jumps out of expression
2718  // evaluation through the shared cleanup block.
2719  Scope.ForceCleanup({&V});
2720  return V;
2721 }
2722 
2723 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2724 // Unary Operators
2725 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2726 
2727 static BinOpInfo createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E,
2728  llvm::Value *InVal, bool IsInc,
2729  FPOptions FPFeatures) {
2730  BinOpInfo BinOp;
2731  BinOp.LHS = InVal;
2732  BinOp.RHS = llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal->getType(), 1, false);
2733  BinOp.Ty = E->getType();
2734  BinOp.Opcode = IsInc ? BO_Add : BO_Sub;
2735  BinOp.FPFeatures = FPFeatures;
2736  BinOp.E = E;
2737  return BinOp;
2738 }
2739 
2740 llvm::Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitIncDecConsiderOverflowBehavior(
2741  const UnaryOperator *E, llvm::Value *InVal, bool IsInc) {
2742  llvm::Value *Amount =
2743  llvm::ConstantInt::get(InVal->getType(), IsInc ? 1 : -1, true);
2744  StringRef Name = IsInc ? "inc" : "dec";
2745  switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
2746  case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
2747  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
2748  return Builder.CreateAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2749  [[fallthrough]];
2750  case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
2751  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
2752  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2753  [[fallthrough]];
2754  case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
2755  if (!E->canOverflow())
2756  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(InVal, Amount, Name);
2757  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(
2758  E, InVal, IsInc, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts())));
2759  }
2760  llvm_unreachable("Unknown SignedOverflowBehaviorTy");
2761 }
2762 
2763 namespace {
2764 /// Handles check and update for lastprivate conditional variables.
2765 class OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII {
2766 private:
2767  CodeGenFunction &CGF;
2768  const UnaryOperator *E;
2769 
2770 public:
2771  OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2772  const UnaryOperator *E)
2773  : CGF(CGF), E(E) {}
2774  ~OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII() {
2775  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP)
2776  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(
2777  CGF, E->getSubExpr());
2778  }
2779 };
2780 } // namespace
2781 
2782 llvm::Value *
2783 ScalarExprEmitter::EmitScalarPrePostIncDec(const UnaryOperator *E, LValue LV,
2784  bool isInc, bool isPre) {
2785  OMPLastprivateConditionalUpdateRAII OMPRegion(CGF, E);
2786  QualType type = E->getSubExpr()->getType();
2787  llvm::PHINode *atomicPHI = nullptr;
2788  llvm::Value *value;
2789  llvm::Value *input;
2790  llvm::Value *Previous = nullptr;
2791  QualType SrcType = E->getType();
2792 
2793  int amount = (isInc ? 1 : -1);
2794  bool isSubtraction = !isInc;
2795 
2796  if (const AtomicType *atomicTy = type->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
2797  type = atomicTy->getValueType();
2798  if (isInc && type->isBooleanType()) {
2799  llvm::Value *True = CGF.EmitToMemory(Builder.getTrue(), type);
2800  if (isPre) {
2801  Builder.CreateStore(True, LV.getAddress(CGF), LV.isVolatileQualified())
2802  ->setAtomic(llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2803  return Builder.getTrue();
2804  }
2805  // For atomic bool increment, we just store true and return it for
2806  // preincrement, do an atomic swap with true for postincrement
2807  return Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(
2808  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg, LV.getAddress(CGF), True,
2809  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2810  }
2811  // Special case for atomic increment / decrement on integers, emit
2812  // atomicrmw instructions. We skip this if we want to be doing overflow
2813  // checking, and fall into the slow path with the atomic cmpxchg loop.
2814  if (!type->isBooleanType() && type->isIntegerType() &&
2815  !(type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
2816  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
2817  CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior() !=
2818  LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
2819  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp aop = isInc ? llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add :
2820  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
2821  llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps op = isInc ? llvm::Instruction::Add :
2822  llvm::Instruction::Sub;
2823  llvm::Value *amt = CGF.EmitToMemory(
2824  llvm::ConstantInt::get(ConvertType(type), 1, true), type);
2825  llvm::Value *old =
2826  Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(aop, LV.getAddress(CGF), amt,
2827  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
2828  return isPre ? Builder.CreateBinOp(op, old, amt) : old;
2829  }
2830  value = EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, E->getExprLoc());
2831  input = value;
2832  // For every other atomic operation, we need to emit a load-op-cmpxchg loop
2833  llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
2834  llvm::BasicBlock *opBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_op", CGF.CurFn);
2835  value = CGF.EmitToMemory(value, type);
2836  Builder.CreateBr(opBB);
2837  Builder.SetInsertPoint(opBB);
2838  atomicPHI = Builder.CreatePHI(value->getType(), 2);
2839  atomicPHI->addIncoming(value, startBB);
2840  value = atomicPHI;
2841  } else {
2842  value = EmitLoadOfLValue(LV, E->getExprLoc());
2843  input = value;
2844  }
2845 
2846  // Special case of integer increment that we have to check first: bool++.
2847  // Due to promotion rules, we get:
2848  // bool++ -> bool = bool + 1
2849  // -> bool = (int)bool + 1
2850  // -> bool = ((int)bool + 1 != 0)
2851  // An interesting aspect of this is that increment is always true.
2852  // Decrement does not have this property.
2853  if (isInc && type->isBooleanType()) {
2854  value = Builder.getTrue();
2855 
2856  // Most common case by far: integer increment.
2857  } else if (type->isIntegerType()) {
2858  QualType promotedType;
2859  bool canPerformLossyDemotionCheck = false;
2860  if (CGF.getContext().isPromotableIntegerType(type)) {
2861  promotedType = CGF.getContext().getPromotedIntegerType(type);
2862  assert(promotedType != type && "Shouldn't promote to the same type.");
2863  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck = true;
2864  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck &=
2865  CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(type) !=
2866  CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(promotedType);
2867  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck &=
2868  PromotionIsPotentiallyEligibleForImplicitIntegerConversionCheck(
2869  type, promotedType);
2870  assert((!canPerformLossyDemotionCheck ||
2871  type->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() ||
2872  promotedType->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() ||
2873  ConvertType(type)->getScalarSizeInBits() ==
2874  ConvertType(promotedType)->getScalarSizeInBits()) &&
2875  "The following check expects that if we do promotion to different "
2876  "underlying canonical type, at least one of the types (either "
2877  "base or promoted) will be signed, or the bitwidths will match.");
2878  }
2879  if (CGF.SanOpts.hasOneOf(
2880  SanitizerKind::ImplicitIntegerArithmeticValueChange |
2881  SanitizerKind::ImplicitBitfieldConversion) &&
2882  canPerformLossyDemotionCheck) {
2883  // While `x += 1` (for `x` with width less than int) is modeled as
2884  // promotion+arithmetics+demotion, and we can catch lossy demotion with
2885  // ease; inc/dec with width less than int can't overflow because of
2886  // promotion rules, so we omit promotion+demotion, which means that we can
2887  // not catch lossy "demotion". Because we still want to catch these cases
2888  // when the sanitizer is enabled, we perform the promotion, then perform
2889  // the increment/decrement in the wider type, and finally
2890  // perform the demotion. This will catch lossy demotions.
2891 
2892  // We have a special case for bitfields defined using all the bits of the
2893  // type. In this case we need to do the same trick as for the integer
2894  // sanitizer checks, i.e., promotion -> increment/decrement -> demotion.
2895 
2896  value = EmitScalarConversion(value, type, promotedType, E->getExprLoc());
2897  Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount, true);
2898  value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2899  // Do pass non-default ScalarConversionOpts so that sanitizer check is
2900  // emitted if LV is not a bitfield, otherwise the bitfield sanitizer
2901  // checks will take care of the conversion.
2902  ScalarConversionOpts Opts;
2903  if (!LV.isBitField())
2904  Opts = ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts);
2905  else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ImplicitBitfieldConversion)) {
2906  Previous = value;
2907  SrcType = promotedType;
2908  }
2909 
2910  value = EmitScalarConversion(value, promotedType, type, E->getExprLoc(),
2911  Opts);
2912 
2913  // Note that signed integer inc/dec with width less than int can't
2914  // overflow because of promotion rules; we're just eliding a few steps
2915  // here.
2916  } else if (E->canOverflow() && type->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
2917  value = EmitIncDecConsiderOverflowBehavior(E, value, isInc);
2918  } else if (E->canOverflow() && type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
2919  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) {
2920  value = EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(createBinOpInfoFromIncDec(
2921  E, value, isInc, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts())));
2922  } else {
2923  llvm::Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount, true);
2924  value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2925  }
2926 
2927  // Next most common: pointer increment.
2928  } else if (const PointerType *ptr = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
2929  QualType type = ptr->getPointeeType();
2930 
2931  // VLA types don't have constant size.
2932  if (const VariableArrayType *vla
2933  = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(type)) {
2934  llvm::Value *numElts = CGF.getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
2935  if (!isInc) numElts = Builder.CreateNSWNeg(numElts, "vla.negsize");
2936  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(vla->getElementType());
2937  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2938  value = Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, value, numElts, "vla.inc");
2939  else
2940  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
2941  elemTy, value, numElts, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2942  E->getExprLoc(), "vla.inc");
2943 
2944  // Arithmetic on function pointers (!) is just +-1.
2945  } else if (type->isFunctionType()) {
2946  llvm::Value *amt = Builder.getInt32(amount);
2947 
2948  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2949  value = Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, value, amt, "incdec.funcptr");
2950  else
2951  value =
2952  CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, value, amt,
2953  /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2954  E->getExprLoc(), "incdec.funcptr");
2955 
2956  // For everything else, we can just do a simple increment.
2957  } else {
2958  llvm::Value *amt = Builder.getInt32(amount);
2959  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(type);
2960  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
2961  value = Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, value, amt, "incdec.ptr");
2962  else
2963  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
2964  elemTy, value, amt, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
2965  E->getExprLoc(), "incdec.ptr");
2966  }
2967 
2968  // Vector increment/decrement.
2969  } else if (type->isVectorType()) {
2970  if (type->hasIntegerRepresentation()) {
2971  llvm::Value *amt = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), amount);
2972 
2973  value = Builder.CreateAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2974  } else {
2975  value = Builder.CreateFAdd(
2976  value,
2977  llvm::ConstantFP::get(value->getType(), amount),
2978  isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
2979  }
2980 
2981  // Floating point.
2982  } else if (type->isRealFloatingType()) {
2983  // Add the inc/dec to the real part.
2984  llvm::Value *amt;
2985  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, E);
2986 
2987  if (type->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
2988  // Another special case: half FP increment should be done via float
2989  if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
2990  value = Builder.CreateCall(
2991  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16,
2992  CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
2993  input, "incdec.conv");
2994  } else {
2995  value = Builder.CreateFPExt(input, CGF.CGM.FloatTy, "incdec.conv");
2996  }
2997  }
2998 
2999  if (value->getType()->isFloatTy())
3000  amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext,
3001  llvm::APFloat(static_cast<float>(amount)));
3002  else if (value->getType()->isDoubleTy())
3003  amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext,
3004  llvm::APFloat(static_cast<double>(amount)));
3005  else {
3006  // Remaining types are Half, Bfloat16, LongDouble, __ibm128 or __float128.
3007  // Convert from float.
3008  llvm::APFloat F(static_cast<float>(amount));
3009  bool ignored;
3010  const llvm::fltSemantics *FS;
3011  // Don't use getFloatTypeSemantics because Half isn't
3012  // necessarily represented using the "half" LLVM type.
3013  if (value->getType()->isFP128Ty())
3014  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getFloat128Format();
3015  else if (value->getType()->isHalfTy())
3016  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getHalfFormat();
3017  else if (value->getType()->isBFloatTy())
3018  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getBFloat16Format();
3019  else if (value->getType()->isPPC_FP128Ty())
3020  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getIbm128Format();
3021  else
3022  FS = &CGF.getTarget().getLongDoubleFormat();
3023  F.convert(*FS, llvm::APFloat::rmTowardZero, &ignored);
3024  amt = llvm::ConstantFP::get(VMContext, F);
3025  }
3026  value = Builder.CreateFAdd(value, amt, isInc ? "inc" : "dec");
3027 
3028  if (type->isHalfType() && !CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().NativeHalfType) {
3029  if (CGF.getContext().getTargetInfo().useFP16ConversionIntrinsics()) {
3030  value = Builder.CreateCall(
3031  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16,
3032  CGF.CGM.FloatTy),
3033  value, "incdec.conv");
3034  } else {
3035  value = Builder.CreateFPTrunc(value, input->getType(), "incdec.conv");
3036  }
3037  }
3038 
3039  // Fixed-point types.
3040  } else if (type->isFixedPointType()) {
3041  // Fixed-point types are tricky. In some cases, it isn't possible to
3042  // represent a 1 or a -1 in the type at all. Piggyback off of
3043  // EmitFixedPointBinOp to avoid having to reimplement saturation.
3044  BinOpInfo Info;
3045  Info.E = E;
3046  Info.Ty = E->getType();
3047  Info.Opcode = isInc ? BO_Add : BO_Sub;
3048  Info.LHS = value;
3049  Info.RHS = llvm::ConstantInt::get(value->getType(), 1, false);
3050  // If the type is signed, it's better to represent this as +(-1) or -(-1),
3051  // since -1 is guaranteed to be representable.
3052  if (type->isSignedFixedPointType()) {
3053  Info.Opcode = isInc ? BO_Sub : BO_Add;
3054  Info.RHS = Builder.CreateNeg(Info.RHS);
3055  }
3056  // Now, convert from our invented integer literal to the type of the unary
3057  // op. This will upscale and saturate if necessary. This value can become
3058  // undef in some cases.
3059  llvm::FixedPointBuilder<CGBuilderTy> FPBuilder(Builder);
3060  auto DstSema = CGF.getContext().getFixedPointSemantics(Info.Ty);
3061  Info.RHS = FPBuilder.CreateIntegerToFixed(Info.RHS, true, DstSema);
3062  value = EmitFixedPointBinOp(Info);
3063 
3064  // Objective-C pointer types.
3065  } else {
3066  const ObjCObjectPointerType *OPT = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
3067 
3068  CharUnits size = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(OPT->getObjectType());
3069  if (!isInc) size = -size;
3070  llvm::Value *sizeValue =
3071  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, size.getQuantity());
3072 
3073  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
3074  value = Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, value, sizeValue, "incdec.objptr");
3075  else
3076  value = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
3077  CGF.Int8Ty, value, sizeValue, /*SignedIndices=*/false, isSubtraction,
3078  E->getExprLoc(), "incdec.objptr");
3079  value = Builder.CreateBitCast(value, input->getType());
3080  }
3081 
3082  if (atomicPHI) {
3083  llvm::BasicBlock *curBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3084  llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont", CGF.CurFn);
3085  auto Pair = CGF.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
3086  LV, RValue::get(atomicPHI), RValue::get(value), E->getExprLoc());
3087  llvm::Value *old = CGF.EmitToMemory(Pair.first.getScalarVal(), type);
3088  llvm::Value *success = Pair.second;
3089  atomicPHI->addIncoming(old, curBlock);
3090  Builder.CreateCondBr(success, contBB, atomicPHI->getParent());
3091  Builder.SetInsertPoint(contBB);
3092  return isPre ? value : input;
3093  }
3094 
3095  // Store the updated result through the lvalue.
3096  if (LV.isBitField()) {
3097  Value *Src = Previous ? Previous : value;
3098  CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(value), LV, &value);
3099  CGF.EmitBitfieldConversionCheck(Src, SrcType, value, E->getType(),
3100  LV.getBitFieldInfo(), E->getExprLoc());
3101  } else
3102  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(value), LV);
3103 
3104  // If this is a postinc, return the value read from memory, otherwise use the
3105  // updated value.
3106  return isPre ? value : input;
3107 }
3108 
3109 
3110 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryPlus(const UnaryOperator *E,
3111  QualType PromotionType) {
3112  QualType promotionTy = PromotionType.isNull()
3113  ? getPromotionType(E->getSubExpr()->getType())
3114  : PromotionType;
3115  Value *result = VisitPlus(E, promotionTy);
3116  if (result && !promotionTy.isNull())
3117  result = EmitUnPromotedValue(result, E->getType());
3118  return result;
3119 }
3120 
3121 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitPlus(const UnaryOperator *E,
3122  QualType PromotionType) {
3123  // This differs from gcc, though, most likely due to a bug in gcc.
3124  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3125  if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3126  return CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(E->getSubExpr(), PromotionType);
3127  return Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3128 }
3129 
3130 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryMinus(const UnaryOperator *E,
3131  QualType PromotionType) {
3132  QualType promotionTy = PromotionType.isNull()
3133  ? getPromotionType(E->getSubExpr()->getType())
3134  : PromotionType;
3135  Value *result = VisitMinus(E, promotionTy);
3136  if (result && !promotionTy.isNull())
3137  result = EmitUnPromotedValue(result, E->getType());
3138  return result;
3139 }
3140 
3141 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitMinus(const UnaryOperator *E,
3142  QualType PromotionType) {
3143  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3144  Value *Op;
3145  if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3146  Op = CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(E->getSubExpr(), PromotionType);
3147  else
3148  Op = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3149 
3150  // Generate a unary FNeg for FP ops.
3151  if (Op->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy())
3152  return Builder.CreateFNeg(Op, "fneg");
3153 
3154  // Emit unary minus with EmitSub so we handle overflow cases etc.
3155  BinOpInfo BinOp;
3156  BinOp.RHS = Op;
3157  BinOp.LHS = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(BinOp.RHS->getType());
3158  BinOp.Ty = E->getType();
3159  BinOp.Opcode = BO_Sub;
3160  BinOp.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts());
3161  BinOp.E = E;
3162  return EmitSub(BinOp);
3163 }
3164 
3165 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryNot(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3166  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3167  Value *Op = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3168  return Builder.CreateNot(Op, "not");
3169 }
3170 
3171 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryLNot(const UnaryOperator *E) {
3172  // Perform vector logical not on comparison with zero vector.
3173  if (E->getType()->isVectorType() &&
3174  E->getType()->castAs<VectorType>()->getVectorKind() ==
3175  VectorKind::Generic) {
3176  Value *Oper = Visit(E->getSubExpr());
3177  Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Oper->getType());
3178  Value *Result;
3179  if (Oper->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3180  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(
3181  CGF, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts()));
3182  Result = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_OEQ, Oper, Zero, "cmp");
3183  } else
3184  Result = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Oper, Zero, "cmp");
3185  return Builder.CreateSExt(Result, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
3186  }
3187 
3188  // Compare operand to zero.
3189  Value *BoolVal = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getSubExpr());
3190 
3191  // Invert value.
3192  // TODO: Could dynamically modify easy computations here. For example, if
3193  // the operand is an icmp ne, turn into icmp eq.
3194  BoolVal = Builder.CreateNot(BoolVal, "lnot");
3195 
3196  // ZExt result to the expr type.
3197  return Builder.CreateZExt(BoolVal, ConvertType(E->getType()), "lnot.ext");
3198 }
3199 
3200 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
3201  // Try folding the offsetof to a constant.
3202  Expr::EvalResult EVResult;
3203  if (E->EvaluateAsInt(EVResult, CGF.getContext())) {
3204  llvm::APSInt Value = EVResult.Val.getInt();
3205  return Builder.getInt(Value);
3206  }
3207 
3208  // Loop over the components of the offsetof to compute the value.
3209  unsigned n = E->getNumComponents();
3210  llvm::Type* ResultType = ConvertType(E->getType());
3211  llvm::Value* Result = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResultType);
3212  QualType CurrentType = E->getTypeSourceInfo()->getType();
3213  for (unsigned i = 0; i != n; ++i) {
3214  OffsetOfNode ON = E->getComponent(i);
3215  llvm::Value *Offset = nullptr;
3216  switch (ON.getKind()) {
3217  case OffsetOfNode::Array: {
3218  // Compute the index
3219  Expr *IdxExpr = E->getIndexExpr(ON.getArrayExprIndex());
3220  llvm::Value* Idx = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(IdxExpr);
3221  bool IdxSigned = IdxExpr->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3222  Idx = Builder.CreateIntCast(Idx, ResultType, IdxSigned, "conv");
3223 
3224  // Save the element type
3225  CurrentType =
3226  CGF.getContext().getAsArrayType(CurrentType)->getElementType();
3227 
3228  // Compute the element size
3229  llvm::Value* ElemSize = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType,
3230  CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(CurrentType).getQuantity());
3231 
3232  // Multiply out to compute the result
3233  Offset = Builder.CreateMul(Idx, ElemSize);
3234  break;
3235  }
3236 
3237  case OffsetOfNode::Field: {
3238  FieldDecl *MemberDecl = ON.getField();
3239  RecordDecl *RD = CurrentType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
3240  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3241 
3242  // Compute the index of the field in its parent.
3243  unsigned i = 0;
3244  // FIXME: It would be nice if we didn't have to loop here!
3245  for (RecordDecl::field_iterator Field = RD->field_begin(),
3246  FieldEnd = RD->field_end();
3247  Field != FieldEnd; ++Field, ++i) {
3248  if (*Field == MemberDecl)
3249  break;
3250  }
3251  assert(i < RL.getFieldCount() && "offsetof field in wrong type");
3252 
3253  // Compute the offset to the field
3254  int64_t OffsetInt = RL.getFieldOffset(i) /
3255  CGF.getContext().getCharWidth();
3256  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType, OffsetInt);
3257 
3258  // Save the element type.
3259  CurrentType = MemberDecl->getType();
3260  break;
3261  }
3262 
3263  case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
3264  llvm_unreachable("dependent __builtin_offsetof");
3265 
3266  case OffsetOfNode::Base: {
3267  if (ON.getBase()->isVirtual()) {
3268  CGF.ErrorUnsupported(E, "virtual base in offsetof");
3269  continue;
3270  }
3271 
3272  RecordDecl *RD = CurrentType->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
3273  const ASTRecordLayout &RL = CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
3274 
3275  // Save the element type.
3276  CurrentType = ON.getBase()->getType();
3277 
3278  // Compute the offset to the base.
3279  auto *BaseRT = CurrentType->castAs<RecordType>();
3280  auto *BaseRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BaseRT->getDecl());
3281  CharUnits OffsetInt = RL.getBaseClassOffset(BaseRD);
3282  Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResultType, OffsetInt.getQuantity());
3283  break;
3284  }
3285  }
3286  Result = Builder.CreateAdd(Result, Offset);
3287  }
3288  return Result;
3289 }
3290 
3291 /// VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr - Return the size or alignment of the type of
3292 /// argument of the sizeof expression as an integer.
3293 Value *
3294 ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(
3295  const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
3296  QualType TypeToSize = E->getTypeOfArgument();
3297  if (auto Kind = E->getKind();
3298  Kind == UETT_SizeOf || Kind == UETT_DataSizeOf) {
3299  if (const VariableArrayType *VAT =
3300  CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(TypeToSize)) {
3301  if (E->isArgumentType()) {
3302  // sizeof(type) - make sure to emit the VLA size.
3303  CGF.EmitVariablyModifiedType(TypeToSize);
3304  } else {
3305  // C99 6.5.3.4p2: If the argument is an expression of type
3306  // VLA, it is evaluated.
3307  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getArgumentExpr());
3308  }
3309 
3310  auto VlaSize = CGF.getVLASize(VAT);
3311  llvm::Value *size = VlaSize.NumElts;
3312 
3313  // Scale the number of non-VLA elements by the non-VLA element size.
3314  CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(VlaSize.Type);
3315  if (!eltSize.isOne())
3316  size = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(CGF.CGM.getSize(eltSize), size);
3317 
3318  return size;
3319  }
3320  } else if (E->getKind() == UETT_OpenMPRequiredSimdAlign) {
3321  auto Alignment =
3322  CGF.getContext()
3323  .toCharUnitsFromBits(CGF.getContext().getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(
3324  E->getTypeOfArgument()->getPointeeType()))
3325  .getQuantity();
3326  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, Alignment);
3327  } else if (E->getKind() == UETT_VectorElements) {
3328  auto *VecTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(ConvertType(E->getTypeOfArgument()));
3329  return Builder.CreateElementCount(CGF.SizeTy, VecTy->getElementCount());
3330  }
3331 
3332  // If this isn't sizeof(vla), the result must be constant; use the constant
3333  // folding logic so we don't have to duplicate it here.
3334  return Builder.getInt(E->EvaluateKnownConstInt(CGF.getContext()));
3335 }
3336 
3337 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryReal(const UnaryOperator *E,
3338  QualType PromotionType) {
3339  QualType promotionTy = PromotionType.isNull()
3340  ? getPromotionType(E->getSubExpr()->getType())
3341  : PromotionType;
3342  Value *result = VisitReal(E, promotionTy);
3343  if (result && !promotionTy.isNull())
3344  result = EmitUnPromotedValue(result, E->getType());
3345  return result;
3346 }
3347 
3348 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitReal(const UnaryOperator *E,
3349  QualType PromotionType) {
3350  Expr *Op = E->getSubExpr();
3351  if (Op->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
3352  // If it's an l-value, load through the appropriate subobject l-value.
3353  // Note that we have to ask E because Op might be an l-value that
3354  // this won't work for, e.g. an Obj-C property.
3355  if (E->isGLValue()) {
3356  if (!PromotionType.isNull()) {
3357  CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy result = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(
3358  Op, /*IgnoreReal*/ IgnoreResultAssign, /*IgnoreImag*/ true);
3359  if (result.first)
3360  result.first = CGF.EmitPromotedValue(result, PromotionType).first;
3361  return result.first;
3362  } else {
3363  return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(CGF.EmitLValue(E), E->getExprLoc())
3364  .getScalarVal();
3365  }
3366  }
3367  // Otherwise, calculate and project.
3368  return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(Op, false, true).first;
3369  }
3370 
3371  if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3372  return CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(Op, PromotionType);
3373  return Visit(Op);
3374 }
3375 
3376 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitUnaryImag(const UnaryOperator *E,
3377  QualType PromotionType) {
3378  QualType promotionTy = PromotionType.isNull()
3379  ? getPromotionType(E->getSubExpr()->getType())
3380  : PromotionType;
3381  Value *result = VisitImag(E, promotionTy);
3382  if (result && !promotionTy.isNull())
3383  result = EmitUnPromotedValue(result, E->getType());
3384  return result;
3385 }
3386 
3387 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitImag(const UnaryOperator *E,
3388  QualType PromotionType) {
3389  Expr *Op = E->getSubExpr();
3390  if (Op->getType()->isAnyComplexType()) {
3391  // If it's an l-value, load through the appropriate subobject l-value.
3392  // Note that we have to ask E because Op might be an l-value that
3393  // this won't work for, e.g. an Obj-C property.
3394  if (Op->isGLValue()) {
3395  if (!PromotionType.isNull()) {
3396  CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy result = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(
3397  Op, /*IgnoreReal*/ true, /*IgnoreImag*/ IgnoreResultAssign);
3398  if (result.second)
3399  result.second = CGF.EmitPromotedValue(result, PromotionType).second;
3400  return result.second;
3401  } else {
3402  return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(CGF.EmitLValue(E), E->getExprLoc())
3403  .getScalarVal();
3404  }
3405  }
3406  // Otherwise, calculate and project.
3407  return CGF.EmitComplexExpr(Op, true, false).second;
3408  }
3409 
3410  // __imag on a scalar returns zero. Emit the subexpr to ensure side
3411  // effects are evaluated, but not the actual value.
3412  if (Op->isGLValue())
3413  CGF.EmitLValue(Op);
3414  else if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3415  CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(Op, PromotionType);
3416  else
3417  CGF.EmitScalarExpr(Op, true);
3418  if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3419  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(PromotionType));
3420  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(E->getType()));
3421 }
3422 
3423 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3424 // Binary Operators
3425 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3426 
3427 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitPromotedValue(Value *result,
3428  QualType PromotionType) {
3429  return CGF.Builder.CreateFPExt(result, ConvertType(PromotionType), "ext");
3430 }
3431 
3432 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitUnPromotedValue(Value *result,
3433  QualType ExprType) {
3434  return CGF.Builder.CreateFPTrunc(result, ConvertType(ExprType), "unpromotion");
3435 }
3436 
3437 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitPromoted(const Expr *E, QualType PromotionType) {
3438  E = E->IgnoreParens();
3439  if (auto BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(E)) {
3440  switch (BO->getOpcode()) {
3441 #define HANDLE_BINOP(OP) \
3442  case BO_##OP: \
3443  return Emit##OP(EmitBinOps(BO, PromotionType));
3444  HANDLE_BINOP(Add)
3445  HANDLE_BINOP(Sub)
3446  HANDLE_BINOP(Mul)
3447  HANDLE_BINOP(Div)
3448 #undef HANDLE_BINOP
3449  default:
3450  break;
3451  }
3452  } else if (auto UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(E)) {
3453  switch (UO->getOpcode()) {
3454  case UO_Imag:
3455  return VisitImag(UO, PromotionType);
3456  case UO_Real:
3457  return VisitReal(UO, PromotionType);
3458  case UO_Minus:
3459  return VisitMinus(UO, PromotionType);
3460  case UO_Plus:
3461  return VisitPlus(UO, PromotionType);
3462  default:
3463  break;
3464  }
3465  }
3466  auto result = Visit(const_cast<Expr *>(E));
3467  if (result) {
3468  if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3469  return EmitPromotedValue(result, PromotionType);
3470  else
3471  return EmitUnPromotedValue(result, E->getType());
3472  }
3473  return result;
3474 }
3475 
3476 BinOpInfo ScalarExprEmitter::EmitBinOps(const BinaryOperator *E,
3477  QualType PromotionType) {
3478  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3479  BinOpInfo Result;
3480  Result.LHS = CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(E->getLHS(), PromotionType);
3481  Result.RHS = CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(E->getRHS(), PromotionType);
3482  if (!PromotionType.isNull())
3483  Result.Ty = PromotionType;
3484  else
3485  Result.Ty = E->getType();
3486  Result.Opcode = E->getOpcode();
3487  Result.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts());
3488  Result.E = E;
3489  return Result;
3490 }
3491 
3492 LValue ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompoundAssignLValue(
3493  const CompoundAssignOperator *E,
3494  Value *(ScalarExprEmitter::*Func)(const BinOpInfo &),
3495  Value *&Result) {
3496  QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
3497  BinOpInfo OpInfo;
3498 
3499  if (E->getComputationResultType()->isAnyComplexType())
3500  return CGF.EmitScalarCompoundAssignWithComplex(E, Result);
3501 
3502  // Emit the RHS first. __block variables need to have the rhs evaluated
3503  // first, plus this should improve codegen a little.
3504 
3505  QualType PromotionTypeCR;
3506  PromotionTypeCR = getPromotionType(E->getComputationResultType());
3507  if (PromotionTypeCR.isNull())
3508  PromotionTypeCR = E->getComputationResultType();
3509  QualType PromotionTypeLHS = getPromotionType(E->getComputationLHSType());
3510  QualType PromotionTypeRHS = getPromotionType(E->getRHS()->getType());
3511  if (!PromotionTypeRHS.isNull())
3512  OpInfo.RHS = CGF.EmitPromotedScalarExpr(E->getRHS(), PromotionTypeRHS);
3513  else
3514  OpInfo.RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
3515  OpInfo.Ty = PromotionTypeCR;
3516  OpInfo.Opcode = E->getOpcode();
3517  OpInfo.FPFeatures = E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts());
3518  OpInfo.E = E;
3519  // Load/convert the LHS.
3520  LValue LHSLV = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
3521 
3522  llvm::PHINode *atomicPHI = nullptr;
3523  if (const AtomicType *atomicTy = LHSTy->getAs<AtomicType>()) {
3524  QualType type = atomicTy->getValueType();
3525  if (!type->isBooleanType() && type->isIntegerType() &&
3526  !(type->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
3527  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3528  CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior() !=
3529  LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
3530  llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP;
3531  llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps Op;
3532  switch (OpInfo.Opcode) {
3533  // We don't have atomicrmw operands for *, %, /, <<, >>
3534  case BO_MulAssign: case BO_DivAssign:
3535  case BO_RemAssign:
3536  case BO_ShlAssign:
3537  case BO_ShrAssign:
3538  break;
3539  case BO_AddAssign:
3540  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add;
3541  Op = llvm::Instruction::Add;
3542  break;
3543  case BO_SubAssign:
3544  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
3545  Op = llvm::Instruction::Sub;
3546  break;
3547  case BO_AndAssign:
3548  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::And;
3549  Op = llvm::Instruction::And;
3550  break;
3551  case BO_XorAssign:
3552  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xor;
3553  Op = llvm::Instruction::Xor;
3554  break;
3555  case BO_OrAssign:
3556  AtomicOp = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Or;
3557  Op = llvm::Instruction::Or;
3558  break;
3559  default:
3560  llvm_unreachable("Invalid compound assignment type");
3561  }
3562  if (AtomicOp != llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BAD_BINOP) {
3563  llvm::Value *Amt = CGF.EmitToMemory(
3564  EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.RHS, E->getRHS()->getType(), LHSTy,
3565  E->getExprLoc()),
3566  LHSTy);
3567  Value *OldVal = Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(
3568  AtomicOp, LHSLV.getAddress(CGF), Amt,
3569  llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent);
3570 
3571  // Since operation is atomic, the result type is guaranteed to be the
3572  // same as the input in LLVM terms.
3573  Result = Builder.CreateBinOp(Op, OldVal, Amt);
3574  return LHSLV;
3575  }
3576  }
3577  // FIXME: For floating point types, we should be saving and restoring the
3578  // floating point environment in the loop.
3579  llvm::BasicBlock *startBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3580  llvm::BasicBlock *opBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_op", CGF.CurFn);
3581  OpInfo.LHS = EmitLoadOfLValue(LHSLV, E->getExprLoc());
3582  OpInfo.LHS = CGF.EmitToMemory(OpInfo.LHS, type);
3583  Builder.CreateBr(opBB);
3584  Builder.SetInsertPoint(opBB);
3585  atomicPHI = Builder.CreatePHI(OpInfo.LHS->getType(), 2);
3586  atomicPHI->addIncoming(OpInfo.LHS, startBB);
3587  OpInfo.LHS = atomicPHI;
3588  }
3589  else
3590  OpInfo.LHS = EmitLoadOfLValue(LHSLV, E->getExprLoc());
3591 
3592  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, OpInfo.FPFeatures);
3593  SourceLocation Loc = E->getExprLoc();
3594  if (!PromotionTypeLHS.isNull())
3595  OpInfo.LHS = EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.LHS, LHSTy, PromotionTypeLHS,
3596  E->getExprLoc());
3597  else
3598  OpInfo.LHS = EmitScalarConversion(OpInfo.LHS, LHSTy,
3599  E->getComputationLHSType(), Loc);
3600 
3601  // Expand the binary operator.
3602  Result = (this->*Func)(OpInfo);
3603 
3604  // Convert the result back to the LHS type,
3605  // potentially with Implicit Conversion sanitizer check.
3606  // If LHSLV is a bitfield, use default ScalarConversionOpts
3607  // to avoid emit any implicit integer checks.
3608  Value *Previous = nullptr;
3609  if (LHSLV.isBitField()) {
3610  Previous = Result;
3611  Result = EmitScalarConversion(Result, PromotionTypeCR, LHSTy, Loc);
3612  } else
3613  Result = EmitScalarConversion(Result, PromotionTypeCR, LHSTy, Loc,
3614  ScalarConversionOpts(CGF.SanOpts));
3615 
3616  if (atomicPHI) {
3617  llvm::BasicBlock *curBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3618  llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont", CGF.CurFn);
3619  auto Pair = CGF.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
3620  LHSLV, RValue::get(atomicPHI), RValue::get(Result), E->getExprLoc());
3621  llvm::Value *old = CGF.EmitToMemory(Pair.first.getScalarVal(), LHSTy);
3622  llvm::Value *success = Pair.second;
3623  atomicPHI->addIncoming(old, curBlock);
3624  Builder.CreateCondBr(success, contBB, atomicPHI->getParent());
3625  Builder.SetInsertPoint(contBB);
3626  return LHSLV;
3627  }
3628 
3629  // Store the result value into the LHS lvalue. Bit-fields are handled
3630  // specially because the result is altered by the store, i.e., [C99 6.5.16p1]
3631  // 'An assignment expression has the value of the left operand after the
3632  // assignment...'.
3633  if (LHSLV.isBitField()) {
3634  Value *Src = Previous ? Previous : Result;
3635  QualType SrcType = E->getRHS()->getType();
3636  QualType DstType = E->getLHS()->getType();
3637  CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(Result), LHSLV, &Result);
3638  CGF.EmitBitfieldConversionCheck(Src, SrcType, Result, DstType,
3639  LHSLV.getBitFieldInfo(), E->getExprLoc());
3640  } else
3641  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(Result), LHSLV);
3642 
3643  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenMP)
3644  CGF.CGM.getOpenMPRuntime().checkAndEmitLastprivateConditional(CGF,
3645  E->getLHS());
3646  return LHSLV;
3647 }
3648 
3649 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompoundAssign(const CompoundAssignOperator *E,
3650  Value *(ScalarExprEmitter::*Func)(const BinOpInfo &)) {
3651  bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
3652  Value *RHS = nullptr;
3653  LValue LHS = EmitCompoundAssignLValue(E, Func, RHS);
3654 
3655  // If the result is clearly ignored, return now.
3656  if (Ignore)
3657  return nullptr;
3658 
3659  // The result of an assignment in C is the assigned r-value.
3660  if (!CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3661  return RHS;
3662 
3663  // If the lvalue is non-volatile, return the computed value of the assignment.
3664  if (!LHS.isVolatileQualified())
3665  return RHS;
3666 
3667  // Otherwise, reload the value.
3668  return EmitLoadOfLValue(LHS, E->getExprLoc());
3669 }
3670 
3671 void ScalarExprEmitter::EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(
3672  const BinOpInfo &Ops, llvm::Value *Zero, bool isDiv) {
3673  SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
3674 
3675  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero)) {
3676  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.RHS, Zero),
3677  SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero));
3678  }
3679 
3680  const auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Ops.E);
3681  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow) &&
3682  Ops.Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() &&
3683  !IsWidenedIntegerOp(CGF.getContext(), BO->getLHS()) &&
3684  Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow()) {
3685  llvm::IntegerType *Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Zero->getType());
3686 
3687  llvm::Value *IntMin =
3688  Builder.getInt(llvm::APInt::getSignedMinValue(Ty->getBitWidth()));
3689  llvm::Value *NegOne = llvm::Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty);
3690 
3691  llvm::Value *LHSCmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.LHS, IntMin);
3692  llvm::Value *RHSCmp = Builder.CreateICmpNE(Ops.RHS, NegOne);
3693  llvm::Value *NotOverflow = Builder.CreateOr(LHSCmp, RHSCmp, "or");
3694  Checks.push_back(
3695  std::make_pair(NotOverflow, SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow));
3696  }
3697 
3698  if (Checks.size() > 0)
3699  EmitBinOpCheck(Checks, Ops);
3700 }
3701 
3702 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitDiv(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3703  {
3704  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3705  if ((CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero) ||
3706  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3707  Ops.Ty->isIntegerType() &&
3708  (Ops.mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() || Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())) {
3709  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3710  EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(Ops, Zero, true);
3711  } else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::FloatDivideByZero) &&
3712  Ops.Ty->isRealFloatingType() &&
3713  Ops.mayHaveFloatDivisionByZero()) {
3714  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3715  llvm::Value *NonZero = Builder.CreateFCmpUNE(Ops.RHS, Zero);
3716  EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(NonZero, SanitizerKind::FloatDivideByZero),
3717  Ops);
3718  }
3719  }
3720 
3721  if (Ops.Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
3722  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
3723  // We need to check the types of the operands of the operator to get the
3724  // correct matrix dimensions.
3725  auto *BO = cast<BinaryOperator>(Ops.E);
3726  (void)BO;
3727  assert(
3728  isa<ConstantMatrixType>(BO->getLHS()->getType().getCanonicalType()) &&
3729  "first operand must be a matrix");
3730  assert(BO->getRHS()->getType().getCanonicalType()->isArithmeticType() &&
3731  "second operand must be an arithmetic type");
3732  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, Ops.FPFeatures);
3733  return MB.CreateScalarDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS,
3734  Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation());
3735  }
3736 
3737  if (Ops.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
3738  llvm::Value *Val;
3739  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, Ops.FPFeatures);
3740  Val = Builder.CreateFDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3741  CGF.SetDivFPAccuracy(Val);
3742  return Val;
3743  }
3744  else if (Ops.isFixedPointOp())
3745  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(Ops);
3746  else if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
3747  return Builder.CreateUDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3748  else
3749  return Builder.CreateSDiv(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "div");
3750 }
3751 
3752 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitRem(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3753  // Rem in C can't be a floating point type: C99 6.5.5p2.
3754  if ((CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::IntegerDivideByZero) ||
3755  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) &&
3756  Ops.Ty->isIntegerType() &&
3757  (Ops.mayHaveIntegerDivisionByZero() || Ops.mayHaveIntegerOverflow())) {
3758  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3759  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ConvertType(Ops.Ty));
3760  EmitUndefinedBehaviorIntegerDivAndRemCheck(Ops, Zero, false);
3761  }
3762 
3763  if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
3764  return Builder.CreateURem(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "rem");
3765  else
3766  return Builder.CreateSRem(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, "rem");
3767 }
3768 
3769 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
3770  unsigned IID;
3771  unsigned OpID = 0;
3772  SanitizerHandler OverflowKind;
3773 
3774  bool isSigned = Ops.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3775  switch (Ops.Opcode) {
3776  case BO_Add:
3777  case BO_AddAssign:
3778  OpID = 1;
3779  IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow :
3780  llvm::Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow;
3781  OverflowKind = SanitizerHandler::AddOverflow;
3782  break;
3783  case BO_Sub:
3784  case BO_SubAssign:
3785  OpID = 2;
3786  IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow :
3787  llvm::Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow;
3788  OverflowKind = SanitizerHandler::SubOverflow;
3789  break;
3790  case BO_Mul:
3791  case BO_MulAssign:
3792  OpID = 3;
3793  IID = isSigned ? llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow :
3794  llvm::Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow;
3795  OverflowKind = SanitizerHandler::MulOverflow;
3796  break;
3797  default:
3798  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported operation for overflow detection");
3799  }
3800  OpID <<= 1;
3801  if (isSigned)
3802  OpID |= 1;
3803 
3804  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
3805  llvm::Type *opTy = CGF.CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(Ops.Ty);
3806 
3807  llvm::Function *intrinsic = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(IID, opTy);
3808 
3809  Value *resultAndOverflow = Builder.CreateCall(intrinsic, {Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS});
3810  Value *result = Builder.CreateExtractValue(resultAndOverflow, 0);
3811  Value *overflow = Builder.CreateExtractValue(resultAndOverflow, 1);
3812 
3813  // Handle overflow with llvm.trap if no custom handler has been specified.
3814  const std::string *handlerName =
3815  &CGF.getLangOpts().OverflowHandler;
3816  if (handlerName->empty()) {
3817  // If the signed-integer-overflow sanitizer is enabled, emit a call to its
3818  // runtime. Otherwise, this is a -ftrapv check, so just emit a trap.
3819  if (!isSigned || CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow)) {
3820  llvm::Value *NotOverflow = Builder.CreateNot(overflow);
3821  SanitizerMask Kind = isSigned ? SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow
3822  : SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow;
3823  EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(NotOverflow, Kind), Ops);
3824  } else
3825  CGF.EmitTrapCheck(Builder.CreateNot(overflow), OverflowKind);
3826  return result;
3827  }
3828 
3829  // Branch in case of overflow.
3830  llvm::BasicBlock *initialBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3831  llvm::BasicBlock *continueBB =
3832  CGF.createBasicBlock("nooverflow", CGF.CurFn, initialBB->getNextNode());
3833  llvm::BasicBlock *overflowBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("overflow", CGF.CurFn);
3834 
3835  Builder.CreateCondBr(overflow, overflowBB, continueBB);
3836 
3837  // If an overflow handler is set, then we want to call it and then use its
3838  // result, if it returns.
3839  Builder.SetInsertPoint(overflowBB);
3840 
3841  // Get the overflow handler.
3842  llvm::Type *Int8Ty = CGF.Int8Ty;
3843  llvm::Type *argTypes[] = { CGF.Int64Ty, CGF.Int64Ty, Int8Ty, Int8Ty };
3844  llvm::FunctionType *handlerTy =
3845  llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.Int64Ty, argTypes, true);
3846  llvm::FunctionCallee handler =
3847  CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(handlerTy, *handlerName);
3848 
3849  // Sign extend the args to 64-bit, so that we can use the same handler for
3850  // all types of overflow.
3851  llvm::Value *lhs = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops.LHS, CGF.Int64Ty);
3852  llvm::Value *rhs = Builder.CreateSExt(Ops.RHS, CGF.Int64Ty);
3853 
3854  // Call the handler with the two arguments, the operation, and the size of
3855  // the result.
3856  llvm::Value *handlerArgs[] = {
3857  lhs,
3858  rhs,
3859  Builder.getInt8(OpID),
3860  Builder.getInt8(cast<llvm::IntegerType>(opTy)->getBitWidth())
3861  };
3862  llvm::Value *handlerResult =
3863  CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(handler, handlerArgs);
3864 
3865  // Truncate the result back to the desired size.
3866  handlerResult = Builder.CreateTrunc(handlerResult, opTy);
3867  Builder.CreateBr(continueBB);
3868 
3869  Builder.SetInsertPoint(continueBB);
3870  llvm::PHINode *phi = Builder.CreatePHI(opTy, 2);
3871  phi->addIncoming(result, initialBB);
3872  phi->addIncoming(handlerResult, overflowBB);
3873 
3874  return phi;
3875 }
3876 
3877 /// Emit pointer + index arithmetic.
3878 static Value *emitPointerArithmetic(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
3879  const BinOpInfo &op,
3880  bool isSubtraction) {
3881  // Must have binary (not unary) expr here. Unary pointer
3882  // increment/decrement doesn't use this path.
3883  const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
3884 
3885  Value *pointer = op.LHS;
3886  Expr *pointerOperand = expr->getLHS();
3887  Value *index = op.RHS;
3888  Expr *indexOperand = expr->getRHS();
3889 
3890  // In a subtraction, the LHS is always the pointer.
3891  if (!isSubtraction && !pointer->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
3892  std::swap(pointer, index);
3893  std::swap(pointerOperand, indexOperand);
3894  }
3895 
3896  bool isSigned = indexOperand->getType()->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3897 
3898  unsigned width = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(index->getType())->getBitWidth();
3899  auto &DL = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout();
3900  auto PtrTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(pointer->getType());
3901 
3902  // Some versions of glibc and gcc use idioms (particularly in their malloc
3903  // routines) that add a pointer-sized integer (known to be a pointer value)
3904  // to a null pointer in order to cast the value back to an integer or as
3905  // part of a pointer alignment algorithm. This is undefined behavior, but
3906  // we'd like to be able to compile programs that use it.
3907  //
3908  // Normally, we'd generate a GEP with a null-pointer base here in response
3909  // to that code, but it's also UB to dereference a pointer created that
3910  // way. Instead (as an acknowledged hack to tolerate the idiom) we will
3911  // generate a direct cast of the integer value to a pointer.
3912  //
3913  // The idiom (p = nullptr + N) is not met if any of the following are true:
3914  //
3915  // The operation is subtraction.
3916  // The index is not pointer-sized.
3917  // The pointer type is not byte-sized.
3918  //
3919  if (BinaryOperator::isNullPointerArithmeticExtension(CGF.getContext(),
3920  op.Opcode,
3921  expr->getLHS(),
3922  expr->getRHS()))
3923  return CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(index, pointer->getType());
3924 
3925  if (width != DL.getIndexTypeSizeInBits(PtrTy)) {
3926  // Zero-extend or sign-extend the pointer value according to
3927  // whether the index is signed or not.
3928  index = CGF.Builder.CreateIntCast(index, DL.getIndexType(PtrTy), isSigned,
3929  "idx.ext");
3930  }
3931 
3932  // If this is subtraction, negate the index.
3933  if (isSubtraction)
3934  index = CGF.Builder.CreateNeg(index, "idx.neg");
3935 
3936  if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ArrayBounds))
3937  CGF.EmitBoundsCheck(op.E, pointerOperand, index, indexOperand->getType(),
3938  /*Accessed*/ false);
3939 
3940  const PointerType *pointerType
3941  = pointerOperand->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
3942  if (!pointerType) {
3943  QualType objectType = pointerOperand->getType()
3944  ->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()
3945  ->getPointeeType();
3946  llvm::Value *objectSize
3947  = CGF.CGM.getSize(CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(objectType));
3948 
3949  index = CGF.Builder.CreateMul(index, objectSize);
3950 
3951  Value *result =
3952  CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3953  return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(result, pointer->getType());
3954  }
3955 
3956  QualType elementType = pointerType->getPointeeType();
3957  if (const VariableArrayType *vla
3958  = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(elementType)) {
3959  // The element count here is the total number of non-VLA elements.
3960  llvm::Value *numElements = CGF.getVLASize(vla).NumElts;
3961 
3962  // Effectively, the multiply by the VLA size is part of the GEP.
3963  // GEP indexes are signed, and scaling an index isn't permitted to
3964  // signed-overflow, so we use the same semantics for our explicit
3965  // multiply. We suppress this if overflow is not undefined behavior.
3966  llvm::Type *elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(vla->getElementType());
3967  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined()) {
3968  index = CGF.Builder.CreateMul(index, numElements, "vla.index");
3969  pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3970  } else {
3971  index = CGF.Builder.CreateNSWMul(index, numElements, "vla.index");
3972  pointer = CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
3973  elemTy, pointer, index, isSigned, isSubtraction, op.E->getExprLoc(),
3974  "add.ptr");
3975  }
3976  return pointer;
3977  }
3978 
3979  // Explicitly handle GNU void* and function pointer arithmetic extensions. The
3980  // GNU void* casts amount to no-ops since our void* type is i8*, but this is
3981  // future proof.
3982  llvm::Type *elemTy;
3983  if (elementType->isVoidType() || elementType->isFunctionType())
3984  elemTy = CGF.Int8Ty;
3985  else
3986  elemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(elementType);
3987 
3988  if (CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined())
3989  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(elemTy, pointer, index, "add.ptr");
3990 
3991  return CGF.EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
3992  elemTy, pointer, index, isSigned, isSubtraction, op.E->getExprLoc(),
3993  "add.ptr");
3994 }
3995 
3996 // Construct an fmuladd intrinsic to represent a fused mul-add of MulOp and
3997 // Addend. Use negMul and negAdd to negate the first operand of the Mul or
3998 // the add operand respectively. This allows fmuladd to represent a*b-c, or
3999 // c-a*b. Patterns in LLVM should catch the negated forms and translate them to
4000 // efficient operations.
4001 static Value* buildFMulAdd(llvm::Instruction *MulOp, Value *Addend,
4002  const CodeGenFunction &CGF, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4003  bool negMul, bool negAdd) {
4004  Value *MulOp0 = MulOp->getOperand(0);
4005  Value *MulOp1 = MulOp->getOperand(1);
4006  if (negMul)
4007  MulOp0 = Builder.CreateFNeg(MulOp0, "neg");
4008  if (negAdd)
4009  Addend = Builder.CreateFNeg(Addend, "neg");
4010 
4011  Value *FMulAdd = nullptr;
4012  if (Builder.getIsFPConstrained()) {
4013  assert(isa<llvm::ConstrainedFPIntrinsic>(MulOp) &&
4014  "Only constrained operation should be created when Builder is in FP "
4015  "constrained mode");
4016  FMulAdd = Builder.CreateConstrainedFPCall(
4017  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmuladd,
4018  Addend->getType()),
4019  {MulOp0, MulOp1, Addend});
4020  } else {
4021  FMulAdd = Builder.CreateCall(
4022  CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::fmuladd, Addend->getType()),
4023  {MulOp0, MulOp1, Addend});
4024  }
4025  MulOp->eraseFromParent();
4026 
4027  return FMulAdd;
4028 }
4029 
4030 // Check whether it would be legal to emit an fmuladd intrinsic call to
4031 // represent op and if so, build the fmuladd.
4032 //
4033 // Checks that (a) the operation is fusable, and (b) -ffp-contract=on.
4034 // Does NOT check the type of the operation - it's assumed that this function
4035 // will be called from contexts where it's known that the type is contractable.
4036 static Value* tryEmitFMulAdd(const BinOpInfo &op,
4037  const CodeGenFunction &CGF, CGBuilderTy &Builder,
4038  bool isSub=false) {
4039 
4040  assert((op.Opcode == BO_Add || op.Opcode == BO_AddAssign ||
4041  op.Opcode == BO_Sub || op.Opcode == BO_SubAssign) &&
4042  "Only fadd/fsub can be the root of an fmuladd.");
4043 
4044  // Check whether this op is marked as fusable.
4045  if (!op.FPFeatures.allowFPContractWithinStatement())
4046  return nullptr;
4047 
4048  Value *LHS = op.LHS;
4049  Value *RHS = op.RHS;
4050 
4051  // Peek through fneg to look for fmul. Make sure fneg has no users, and that
4052  // it is the only use of its operand.
4053  bool NegLHS = false;
4054  if (auto *LHSUnOp = dyn_cast<llvm::UnaryOperator>(LHS)) {
4055  if (LHSUnOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FNeg &&
4056  LHSUnOp->use_empty() && LHSUnOp->getOperand(0)->hasOneUse()) {
4057  LHS = LHSUnOp->getOperand(0);
4058  NegLHS = true;
4059  }
4060  }
4061 
4062  bool NegRHS = false;
4063  if (auto *RHSUnOp = dyn_cast<llvm::UnaryOperator>(RHS)) {
4064  if (RHSUnOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FNeg &&
4065  RHSUnOp->use_empty() && RHSUnOp->getOperand(0)->hasOneUse()) {
4066  RHS = RHSUnOp->getOperand(0);
4067  NegRHS = true;
4068  }
4069  }
4070 
4071  // We have a potentially fusable op. Look for a mul on one of the operands.
4072  // Also, make sure that the mul result isn't used directly. In that case,
4073  // there's no point creating a muladd operation.
4074  if (auto *LHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(LHS)) {
4075  if (LHSBinOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FMul &&
4076  (LHSBinOp->use_empty() || NegLHS)) {
4077  // If we looked through fneg, erase it.
4078  if (NegLHS)
4079  cast<llvm::Instruction>(op.LHS)->eraseFromParent();
4080  return buildFMulAdd(LHSBinOp, op.RHS, CGF, Builder, NegLHS, isSub);
4081  }
4082  }
4083  if (auto *RHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::BinaryOperator>(RHS)) {
4084  if (RHSBinOp->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::FMul &&
4085  (RHSBinOp->use_empty() || NegRHS)) {
4086  // If we looked through fneg, erase it.
4087  if (NegRHS)
4088  cast<llvm::Instruction>(op.RHS)->eraseFromParent();
4089  return buildFMulAdd(RHSBinOp, op.LHS, CGF, Builder, isSub ^ NegRHS, false);
4090  }
4091  }
4092 
4093  if (auto *LHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(LHS)) {
4094  if (LHSBinOp->getIntrinsicID() ==
4095  llvm::Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul &&
4096  (LHSBinOp->use_empty() || NegLHS)) {
4097  // If we looked through fneg, erase it.
4098  if (NegLHS)
4099  cast<llvm::Instruction>(op.LHS)->eraseFromParent();
4100  return buildFMulAdd(LHSBinOp, op.RHS, CGF, Builder, NegLHS, isSub);
4101  }
4102  }
4103  if (auto *RHSBinOp = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(RHS)) {
4104  if (RHSBinOp->getIntrinsicID() ==
4105  llvm::Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_fmul &&
4106  (RHSBinOp->use_empty() || NegRHS)) {
4107  // If we looked through fneg, erase it.
4108  if (NegRHS)
4109  cast<llvm::Instruction>(op.RHS)->eraseFromParent();
4110  return buildFMulAdd(RHSBinOp, op.LHS, CGF, Builder, isSub ^ NegRHS, false);
4111  }
4112  }
4113 
4114  return nullptr;
4115 }
4116 
4117 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitAdd(const BinOpInfo &op) {
4118  if (op.LHS->getType()->isPointerTy() ||
4119  op.RHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
4120  return emitPointerArithmetic(CGF, op, CodeGenFunction::NotSubtraction);
4121 
4122  if (op.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
4123  switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
4124  case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
4125  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
4126  return Builder.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
4127  [[fallthrough]];
4128  case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
4129  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
4130  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
4131  [[fallthrough]];
4132  case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
4133  if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
4134  return Builder.CreateNSWAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
4135  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
4136  }
4137  }
4138 
4139  // For vector and matrix adds, try to fold into a fmuladd.
4140  if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4141  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
4142  // Try to form an fmuladd.
4143  if (Value *FMulAdd = tryEmitFMulAdd(op, CGF, Builder))
4144  return FMulAdd;
4145  }
4146 
4147  if (op.Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
4148  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
4149  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
4150  return MB.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS);
4151  }
4152 
4153  if (op.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
4154  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
4155  !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
4156  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
4157 
4158  if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4159  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
4160  return Builder.CreateFAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
4161  }
4162 
4163  if (op.isFixedPointOp())
4164  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(op);
4165 
4166  return Builder.CreateAdd(op.LHS, op.RHS, "add");
4167 }
4168 
4169 /// The resulting value must be calculated with exact precision, so the operands
4170 /// may not be the same type.
4171 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitFixedPointBinOp(const BinOpInfo &op) {
4172  using llvm::APSInt;
4173  using llvm::ConstantInt;
4174 
4175  // This is either a binary operation where at least one of the operands is
4176  // a fixed-point type, or a unary operation where the operand is a fixed-point
4177  // type. The result type of a binary operation is determined by
4178  // Sema::handleFixedPointConversions().
4179  QualType ResultTy = op.Ty;
4180  QualType LHSTy, RHSTy;
4181  if (const auto *BinOp = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E)) {
4182  RHSTy = BinOp->getRHS()->getType();
4183  if (const auto *CAO = dyn_cast<CompoundAssignOperator>(BinOp)) {
4184  // For compound assignment, the effective type of the LHS at this point
4185  // is the computation LHS type, not the actual LHS type, and the final
4186  // result type is not the type of the expression but rather the
4187  // computation result type.
4188  LHSTy = CAO->getComputationLHSType();
4189  ResultTy = CAO->getComputationResultType();
4190  } else
4191  LHSTy = BinOp->getLHS()->getType();
4192  } else if (const auto *UnOp = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(op.E)) {
4193  LHSTy = UnOp->getSubExpr()->getType();
4194  RHSTy = UnOp->getSubExpr()->getType();
4195  }
4196  ASTContext &Ctx = CGF.getContext();
4197  Value *LHS = op.LHS;
4198  Value *RHS = op.RHS;
4199 
4200  auto LHSFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(LHSTy);
4201  auto RHSFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(RHSTy);
4202  auto ResultFixedSema = Ctx.getFixedPointSemantics(ResultTy);
4203  auto CommonFixedSema = LHSFixedSema.getCommonSemantics(RHSFixedSema);
4204 
4205  // Perform the actual operation.
4206  Value *Result;
4207  llvm::FixedPointBuilder<CGBuilderTy> FPBuilder(Builder);
4208  switch (op.Opcode) {
4209  case BO_AddAssign:
4210  case BO_Add:
4211  Result = FPBuilder.CreateAdd(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4212  break;
4213  case BO_SubAssign:
4214  case BO_Sub:
4215  Result = FPBuilder.CreateSub(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4216  break;
4217  case BO_MulAssign:
4218  case BO_Mul:
4219  Result = FPBuilder.CreateMul(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4220  break;
4221  case BO_DivAssign:
4222  case BO_Div:
4223  Result = FPBuilder.CreateDiv(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4224  break;
4225  case BO_ShlAssign:
4226  case BO_Shl:
4227  Result = FPBuilder.CreateShl(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS);
4228  break;
4229  case BO_ShrAssign:
4230  case BO_Shr:
4231  Result = FPBuilder.CreateShr(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS);
4232  break;
4233  case BO_LT:
4234  return FPBuilder.CreateLT(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4235  case BO_GT:
4236  return FPBuilder.CreateGT(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4237  case BO_LE:
4238  return FPBuilder.CreateLE(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4239  case BO_GE:
4240  return FPBuilder.CreateGE(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4241  case BO_EQ:
4242  // For equality operations, we assume any padding bits on unsigned types are
4243  // zero'd out. They could be overwritten through non-saturating operations
4244  // that cause overflow, but this leads to undefined behavior.
4245  return FPBuilder.CreateEQ(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4246  case BO_NE:
4247  return FPBuilder.CreateNE(LHS, LHSFixedSema, RHS, RHSFixedSema);
4248  case BO_Cmp:
4249  case BO_LAnd:
4250  case BO_LOr:
4251  llvm_unreachable("Found unimplemented fixed point binary operation");
4252  case BO_PtrMemD:
4253  case BO_PtrMemI:
4254  case BO_Rem:
4255  case BO_Xor:
4256  case BO_And:
4257  case BO_Or:
4258  case BO_Assign:
4259  case BO_RemAssign:
4260  case BO_AndAssign:
4261  case BO_XorAssign:
4262  case BO_OrAssign:
4263  case BO_Comma:
4264  llvm_unreachable("Found unsupported binary operation for fixed point types.");
4265  }
4266 
4267  bool IsShift = BinaryOperator::isShiftOp(op.Opcode) ||
4268  BinaryOperator::isShiftAssignOp(op.Opcode);
4269  // Convert to the result type.
4270  return FPBuilder.CreateFixedToFixed(Result, IsShift ? LHSFixedSema
4271  : CommonFixedSema,
4272  ResultFixedSema);
4273 }
4274 
4275 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitSub(const BinOpInfo &op) {
4276  // The LHS is always a pointer if either side is.
4277  if (!op.LHS->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
4278  if (op.Ty->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType()) {
4279  switch (CGF.getLangOpts().getSignedOverflowBehavior()) {
4280  case LangOptions::SOB_Defined:
4281  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
4282  return Builder.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4283  [[fallthrough]];
4284  case LangOptions::SOB_Undefined:
4285  if (!CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::SignedIntegerOverflow))
4286  return Builder.CreateNSWSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4287  [[fallthrough]];
