4288  case LangOptions::SOB_Trapping:
4289  if (CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
4290  return Builder.CreateNSWSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4291  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
4292  }
4293  }
4294 
4295  // For vector and matrix subs, try to fold into a fmuladd.
4296  if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4297  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
4298  // Try to form an fmuladd.
4299  if (Value *FMulAdd = tryEmitFMulAdd(op, CGF, Builder, true))
4300  return FMulAdd;
4301  }
4302 
4303  if (op.Ty->isConstantMatrixType()) {
4304  llvm::MatrixBuilder MB(Builder);
4305  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
4306  return MB.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS);
4307  }
4308 
4309  if (op.Ty->isUnsignedIntegerType() &&
4310  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedIntegerOverflow) &&
4311  !CanElideOverflowCheck(CGF.getContext(), op))
4312  return EmitOverflowCheckedBinOp(op);
4313 
4314  if (op.LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4315  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, op.FPFeatures);
4316  return Builder.CreateFSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4317  }
4318 
4319  if (op.isFixedPointOp())
4320  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(op);
4321 
4322  return Builder.CreateSub(op.LHS, op.RHS, "sub");
4323  }
4324 
4325  // If the RHS is not a pointer, then we have normal pointer
4326  // arithmetic.
4327  if (!op.RHS->getType()->isPointerTy())
4328  return emitPointerArithmetic(CGF, op, CodeGenFunction::IsSubtraction);
4329 
4330  // Otherwise, this is a pointer subtraction.
4331 
4332  // Do the raw subtraction part.
4333  llvm::Value *LHS
4334  = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(op.LHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy, "sub.ptr.lhs.cast");
4335  llvm::Value *RHS
4336  = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(op.RHS, CGF.PtrDiffTy, "sub.ptr.rhs.cast");
4337  Value *diffInChars = Builder.CreateSub(LHS, RHS, "sub.ptr.sub");
4338 
4339  // Okay, figure out the element size.
4340  const BinaryOperator *expr = cast<BinaryOperator>(op.E);
4341  QualType elementType = expr->getLHS()->getType()->getPointeeType();
4342 
4343  llvm::Value *divisor = nullptr;
4344 
4345  // For a variable-length array, this is going to be non-constant.
4346  if (const VariableArrayType *vla
4347  = CGF.getContext().getAsVariableArrayType(elementType)) {
4348  auto VlaSize = CGF.getVLASize(vla);
4349  elementType = VlaSize.Type;
4350  divisor = VlaSize.NumElts;
4351 
4352  // Scale the number of non-VLA elements by the non-VLA element size.
4353  CharUnits eltSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType);
4354  if (!eltSize.isOne())
4355  divisor = CGF.Builder.CreateNUWMul(CGF.CGM.getSize(eltSize), divisor);
4356 
4357  // For everything elese, we can just compute it, safe in the
4358  // assumption that Sema won't let anything through that we can't
4359  // safely compute the size of.
4360  } else {
4361  CharUnits elementSize;
4362  // Handle GCC extension for pointer arithmetic on void* and
4363  // function pointer types.
4364  if (elementType->isVoidType() || elementType->isFunctionType())
4365  elementSize = CharUnits::One();
4366  else
4367  elementSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(elementType);
4368 
4369  // Don't even emit the divide for element size of 1.
4370  if (elementSize.isOne())
4371  return diffInChars;
4372 
4373  divisor = CGF.CGM.getSize(elementSize);
4374  }
4375 
4376  // Otherwise, do a full sdiv. This uses the "exact" form of sdiv, since
4377  // pointer difference in C is only defined in the case where both operands
4378  // are pointing to elements of an array.
4379  return Builder.CreateExactSDiv(diffInChars, divisor, "sub.ptr.div");
4380 }
4381 
4382 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::GetMaximumShiftAmount(Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
4383  bool RHSIsSigned) {
4384  llvm::IntegerType *Ty;
4385  if (llvm::VectorType *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(LHS->getType()))
4386  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(VT->getElementType());
4387  else
4388  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(LHS->getType());
4389  // For a given type of LHS the maximum shift amount is width(LHS)-1, however
4390  // it can occur that width(LHS)-1 > range(RHS). Since there is no check for
4391  // this in ConstantInt::get, this results in the value getting truncated.
4392  // Constrain the return value to be max(RHS) in this case.
4393  llvm::Type *RHSTy = RHS->getType();
4394  llvm::APInt RHSMax =
4395  RHSIsSigned ? llvm::APInt::getSignedMaxValue(RHSTy->getScalarSizeInBits())
4396  : llvm::APInt::getMaxValue(RHSTy->getScalarSizeInBits());
4397  if (RHSMax.ult(Ty->getBitWidth()))
4398  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(RHSTy, RHSMax);
4399  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(RHSTy, Ty->getBitWidth() - 1);
4400 }
4401 
4402 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::ConstrainShiftValue(Value *LHS, Value *RHS,
4403  const Twine &Name) {
4404  llvm::IntegerType *Ty;
4405  if (auto *VT = dyn_cast<llvm::VectorType>(LHS->getType()))
4406  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(VT->getElementType());
4407  else
4408  Ty = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(LHS->getType());
4409 
4410  if (llvm::isPowerOf2_64(Ty->getBitWidth()))
4411  return Builder.CreateAnd(RHS, GetMaximumShiftAmount(LHS, RHS, false), Name);
4412 
4413  return Builder.CreateURem(
4414  RHS, llvm::ConstantInt::get(RHS->getType(), Ty->getBitWidth()), Name);
4415 }
4416 
4417 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitShl(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
4418  // TODO: This misses out on the sanitizer check below.
4419  if (Ops.isFixedPointOp())
4420  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(Ops);
4421 
4422  // LLVM requires the LHS and RHS to be the same type: promote or truncate the
4423  // RHS to the same size as the LHS.
4424  Value *RHS = Ops.RHS;
4425  if (Ops.LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
4426  RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(RHS, Ops.LHS->getType(), false, "sh_prom");
4427 
4428  bool SanitizeSignedBase = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftBase) &&
4429  Ops.Ty->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() &&
4430  !CGF.getLangOpts().isSignedOverflowDefined() &&
4431  !CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20;
4432  bool SanitizeUnsignedBase =
4433  CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::UnsignedShiftBase) &&
4434  Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation();
4435  bool SanitizeBase = SanitizeSignedBase || SanitizeUnsignedBase;
4436  bool SanitizeExponent = CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent);
4437  // OpenCL 6.3j: shift values are effectively % word size of LHS.
4438  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL || CGF.getLangOpts().HLSL)
4439  RHS = ConstrainShiftValue(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shl.mask");
4440  else if ((SanitizeBase || SanitizeExponent) &&
4441  isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ops.LHS->getType())) {
4442  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
4443  SmallVector<std::pair<Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
4444  bool RHSIsSigned = Ops.rhsHasSignedIntegerRepresentation();
4445  llvm::Value *WidthMinusOne =
4446  GetMaximumShiftAmount(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, RHSIsSigned);
4447  llvm::Value *ValidExponent = Builder.CreateICmpULE(Ops.RHS, WidthMinusOne);
4448 
4449  if (SanitizeExponent) {
4450  Checks.push_back(
4451  std::make_pair(ValidExponent, SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent));
4452  }
4453 
4454  if (SanitizeBase) {
4455  // Check whether we are shifting any non-zero bits off the top of the
4456  // integer. We only emit this check if exponent is valid - otherwise
4457  // instructions below will have undefined behavior themselves.
4458  llvm::BasicBlock *Orig = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4459  llvm::BasicBlock *Cont = CGF.createBasicBlock("cont");
4460  llvm::BasicBlock *CheckShiftBase = CGF.createBasicBlock("check");
4461  Builder.CreateCondBr(ValidExponent, CheckShiftBase, Cont);
4462  llvm::Value *PromotedWidthMinusOne =
4463  (RHS == Ops.RHS) ? WidthMinusOne
4464  : GetMaximumShiftAmount(Ops.LHS, RHS, RHSIsSigned);
4465  CGF.EmitBlock(CheckShiftBase);
4466  llvm::Value *BitsShiftedOff = Builder.CreateLShr(
4467  Ops.LHS, Builder.CreateSub(PromotedWidthMinusOne, RHS, "shl.zeros",
4468  /*NUW*/ true, /*NSW*/ true),
4469  "shl.check");
4470  if (SanitizeUnsignedBase || CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
4471  // In C99, we are not permitted to shift a 1 bit into the sign bit.
4472  // Under C++11's rules, shifting a 1 bit into the sign bit is
4473  // OK, but shifting a 1 bit out of it is not. (C89 and C++03 don't
4474  // define signed left shifts, so we use the C99 and C++11 rules there).
4475  // Unsigned shifts can always shift into the top bit.
4476  llvm::Value *One = llvm::ConstantInt::get(BitsShiftedOff->getType(), 1);
4477  BitsShiftedOff = Builder.CreateLShr(BitsShiftedOff, One);
4478  }
4479  llvm::Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::get(BitsShiftedOff->getType(), 0);
4480  llvm::Value *ValidBase = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(BitsShiftedOff, Zero);
4481  CGF.EmitBlock(Cont);
4482  llvm::PHINode *BaseCheck = Builder.CreatePHI(ValidBase->getType(), 2);
4483  BaseCheck->addIncoming(Builder.getTrue(), Orig);
4484  BaseCheck->addIncoming(ValidBase, CheckShiftBase);
4485  Checks.push_back(std::make_pair(
4486  BaseCheck, SanitizeSignedBase ? SanitizerKind::ShiftBase
4487  : SanitizerKind::UnsignedShiftBase));
4488  }
4489 
4490  assert(!Checks.empty());
4491  EmitBinOpCheck(Checks, Ops);
4492  }
4493 
4494  return Builder.CreateShl(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shl");
4495 }
4496 
4497 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitShr(const BinOpInfo &Ops) {
4498  // TODO: This misses out on the sanitizer check below.
4499  if (Ops.isFixedPointOp())
4500  return EmitFixedPointBinOp(Ops);
4501 
4502  // LLVM requires the LHS and RHS to be the same type: promote or truncate the
4503  // RHS to the same size as the LHS.
4504  Value *RHS = Ops.RHS;
4505  if (Ops.LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
4506  RHS = Builder.CreateIntCast(RHS, Ops.LHS->getType(), false, "sh_prom");
4507 
4508  // OpenCL 6.3j: shift values are effectively % word size of LHS.
4509  if (CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL || CGF.getLangOpts().HLSL)
4510  RHS = ConstrainShiftValue(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr.mask");
4511  else if (CGF.SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent) &&
4512  isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Ops.LHS->getType())) {
4513  CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
4514  bool RHSIsSigned = Ops.rhsHasSignedIntegerRepresentation();
4515  llvm::Value *Valid = Builder.CreateICmpULE(
4516  Ops.RHS, GetMaximumShiftAmount(Ops.LHS, Ops.RHS, RHSIsSigned));
4517  EmitBinOpCheck(std::make_pair(Valid, SanitizerKind::ShiftExponent), Ops);
4518  }
4519 
4520  if (Ops.Ty->hasUnsignedIntegerRepresentation())
4521  return Builder.CreateLShr(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr");
4522  return Builder.CreateAShr(Ops.LHS, RHS, "shr");
4523 }
4524 
4525 enum IntrinsicType { VCMPEQ, VCMPGT };
4526 // return corresponding comparison intrinsic for given vector type
4527 static llvm::Intrinsic::ID GetIntrinsic(IntrinsicType IT,
4528  BuiltinType::Kind ElemKind) {
4529  switch (ElemKind) {
4530  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected element type");
4531  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
4532  case BuiltinType::UChar:
4533  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequb_p :
4534  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtub_p;
4535  case BuiltinType::Char_S:
4536  case BuiltinType::SChar:
4537  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequb_p :
4538  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsb_p;
4539  case BuiltinType::UShort:
4540  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequh_p :
4541  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuh_p;
4542  case BuiltinType::Short:
4543  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequh_p :
4544  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsh_p;
4545  case BuiltinType::UInt:
4546  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequw_p :
4547  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuw_p;
4548  case BuiltinType::Int:
4549  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequw_p :
4550  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsw_p;
4551  case BuiltinType::ULong:
4552  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
4553  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequd_p :
4554  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtud_p;
4555  case BuiltinType::Long:
4556  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
4557  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequd_p :
4558  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsd_p;
4559  case BuiltinType::Float:
4560  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpeqfp_p :
4561  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtfp_p;
4562  case BuiltinType::Double:
4563  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xvcmpeqdp_p :
4564  llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_xvcmpgtdp_p;
4565  case BuiltinType::UInt128:
4566  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequq_p
4567  : llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtuq_p;
4568  case BuiltinType::Int128:
4569  return (IT == VCMPEQ) ? llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpequq_p
4570  : llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgtsq_p;
4571  }
4572 }
4573 
4574 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::EmitCompare(const BinaryOperator *E,
4575  llvm::CmpInst::Predicate UICmpOpc,
4576  llvm::CmpInst::Predicate SICmpOpc,
4577  llvm::CmpInst::Predicate FCmpOpc,
4578  bool IsSignaling) {
4579  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4580  Value *Result;
4581  QualType LHSTy = E->getLHS()->getType();
4582  QualType RHSTy = E->getRHS()->getType();
4583  if (const MemberPointerType *MPT = LHSTy->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
4584  assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_EQ ||
4585  E->getOpcode() == BO_NE);
4586  Value *LHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getLHS());
4587  Value *RHS = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
4588  Result = CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberPointerComparison(
4589  CGF, LHS, RHS, MPT, E->getOpcode() == BO_NE);
4590  } else if (!LHSTy->isAnyComplexType() && !RHSTy->isAnyComplexType()) {
4591  BinOpInfo BOInfo = EmitBinOps(E);
4592  Value *LHS = BOInfo.LHS;
4593  Value *RHS = BOInfo.RHS;
4594 
4595  // If AltiVec, the comparison results in a numeric type, so we use
4596  // intrinsics comparing vectors and giving 0 or 1 as a result
4597  if (LHSTy->isVectorType() && !E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4598  // constants for mapping CR6 register bits to predicate result
4599  enum { CR6_EQ=0, CR6_EQ_REV, CR6_LT, CR6_LT_REV } CR6;
4600 
4601  llvm::Intrinsic::ID ID = llvm::Intrinsic::not_intrinsic;
4602 
4603  // in several cases vector arguments order will be reversed
4604  Value *FirstVecArg = LHS,
4605  *SecondVecArg = RHS;
4606 
4607  QualType ElTy = LHSTy->castAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
4608  BuiltinType::Kind ElementKind = ElTy->castAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind();
4609 
4610  switch(E->getOpcode()) {
4611  default: llvm_unreachable("is not a comparison operation");
4612  case BO_EQ:
4613  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4614  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPEQ, ElementKind);
4615  break;
4616  case BO_NE:
4617  CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4618  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPEQ, ElementKind);
4619  break;
4620  case BO_LT:
4621  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4622  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4623  std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4624  break;
4625  case BO_GT:
4626  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4627  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4628  break;
4629  case BO_LE:
4630  if (ElementKind == BuiltinType::Float) {
4631  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4632  ID = llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgefp_p;
4633  std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4634  }
4635  else {
4636  CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4637  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4638  }
4639  break;
4640  case BO_GE:
4641  if (ElementKind == BuiltinType::Float) {
4642  CR6 = CR6_LT;
4643  ID = llvm::Intrinsic::ppc_altivec_vcmpgefp_p;
4644  }
4645  else {
4646  CR6 = CR6_EQ;
4647  ID = GetIntrinsic(VCMPGT, ElementKind);
4648  std::swap(FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg);
4649  }
4650  break;
4651  }
4652 
4653  Value *CR6Param = Builder.getInt32(CR6);
4654  llvm::Function *F = CGF.CGM.getIntrinsic(ID);
4655  Result = Builder.CreateCall(F, {CR6Param, FirstVecArg, SecondVecArg});
4656 
4657  // The result type of intrinsic may not be same as E->getType().
4658  // If E->getType() is not BoolTy, EmitScalarConversion will do the
4659  // conversion work. If E->getType() is BoolTy, EmitScalarConversion will
4660  // do nothing, if ResultTy is not i1 at the same time, it will cause
4661  // crash later.
4662  llvm::IntegerType *ResultTy = cast<llvm::IntegerType>(Result->getType());
4663  if (ResultTy->getBitWidth() > 1 &&
4664  E->getType() == CGF.getContext().BoolTy)
4665  Result = Builder.CreateTrunc(Result, Builder.getInt1Ty());
4666  return EmitScalarConversion(Result, CGF.getContext().BoolTy, E->getType(),
4667  E->getExprLoc());
4668  }
4669 
4670  if (BOInfo.isFixedPointOp()) {
4671  Result = EmitFixedPointBinOp(BOInfo);
4672  } else if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4673  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(CGF, BOInfo.FPFeatures);
4674  if (!IsSignaling)
4675  Result = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4676  else
4677  Result = Builder.CreateFCmpS(FCmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4678  } else if (LHSTy->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation()) {
4679  Result = Builder.CreateICmp(SICmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4680  } else {
4681  // Unsigned integers and pointers.
4682 
4683  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
4684  !isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(LHS) &&
4685  !isa<llvm::ConstantPointerNull>(RHS)) {
4686 
4687  // Dynamic information is required to be stripped for comparisons,
4688  // because it could leak the dynamic information. Based on comparisons
4689  // of pointers to dynamic objects, the optimizer can replace one pointer
4690  // with another, which might be incorrect in presence of invariant
4691  // groups. Comparison with null is safe because null does not carry any
4692  // dynamic information.
4693  if (LHSTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
4694  LHS = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(LHS);
4695  if (RHSTy.mayBeDynamicClass())
4696  RHS = Builder.CreateStripInvariantGroup(RHS);
4697  }
4698 
4699  Result = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS, RHS, "cmp");
4700  }
4701 
4702  // If this is a vector comparison, sign extend the result to the appropriate
4703  // vector integer type and return it (don't convert to bool).
4704  if (LHSTy->isVectorType())
4705  return Builder.CreateSExt(Result, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4706 
4707  } else {
4708  // Complex Comparison: can only be an equality comparison.
4709  CodeGenFunction::ComplexPairTy LHS, RHS;
4710  QualType CETy;
4711  if (auto *CTy = LHSTy->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4712  LHS = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E->getLHS());
4713  CETy = CTy->getElementType();
4714  } else {
4715  LHS.first = Visit(E->getLHS());
4716  LHS.second = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(LHS.first->getType());
4717  CETy = LHSTy;
4718  }
4719  if (auto *CTy = RHSTy->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
4720  RHS = CGF.EmitComplexExpr(E->getRHS());
4721  assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(CETy,
4722  CTy->getElementType()) &&
4723  "The element types must always match.");
4724  (void)CTy;
4725  } else {
4726  RHS.first = Visit(E->getRHS());
4727  RHS.second = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(RHS.first->getType());
4728  assert(CGF.getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(CETy, RHSTy) &&
4729  "The element types must always match.");
4730  }
4731 
4732  Value *ResultR, *ResultI;
4733  if (CETy->isRealFloatingType()) {
4734  // As complex comparisons can only be equality comparisons, they
4735  // are never signaling comparisons.
4736  ResultR = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS.first, RHS.first, "cmp.r");
4737  ResultI = Builder.CreateFCmp(FCmpOpc, LHS.second, RHS.second, "cmp.i");
4738  } else {
4739  // Complex comparisons can only be equality comparisons. As such, signed
4740  // and unsigned opcodes are the same.
4741  ResultR = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS.first, RHS.first, "cmp.r");
4742  ResultI = Builder.CreateICmp(UICmpOpc, LHS.second, RHS.second, "cmp.i");
4743  }
4744 
4745  if (E->getOpcode() == BO_EQ) {
4746  Result = Builder.CreateAnd(ResultR, ResultI, "and.ri");
4747  } else {
4748  assert(E->getOpcode() == BO_NE &&
4749  "Complex comparison other than == or != ?");
4750  Result = Builder.CreateOr(ResultR, ResultI, "or.ri");
4751  }
4752  }
4753 
4754  return EmitScalarConversion(Result, CGF.getContext().BoolTy, E->getType(),
4755  E->getExprLoc());
4756 }
4757 
4758 llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitWithOriginalRHSBitfieldAssignment(
4759  const BinaryOperator *E, Value **Previous, QualType *SrcType) {
4760  // In case we have the integer or bitfield sanitizer checks enabled
4761  // we want to get the expression before scalar conversion.
4762  if (auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E->getRHS())) {
4763  CastKind Kind = ICE->getCastKind();
4764  if (Kind == CK_IntegralCast || Kind == CK_LValueToRValue) {
4765  *SrcType = ICE->getSubExpr()->getType();
4766  *Previous = EmitScalarExpr(ICE->getSubExpr());
4767  // Pass default ScalarConversionOpts to avoid emitting
4768  // integer sanitizer checks as E refers to bitfield.
4769  return EmitScalarConversion(*Previous, *SrcType, ICE->getType(),
4770  ICE->getExprLoc());
4771  }
4772  }
4773  return EmitScalarExpr(E->getRHS());
4774 }
4775 
4776 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinAssign(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4777  bool Ignore = TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
4778 
4779  Value *RHS;
4780  LValue LHS;
4781 
4782  switch (E->getLHS()->getType().getObjCLifetime()) {
4783  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4784  std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreStrong(E, Ignore);
4785  break;
4786 
4787  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4788  std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreAutoreleasing(E);
4789  break;
4790 
4791  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4792  std::tie(LHS, RHS) = CGF.EmitARCStoreUnsafeUnretained(E, Ignore);
4793  break;
4794 
4795  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4796  RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4797  LHS = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
4798  RHS = CGF.EmitARCStoreWeak(LHS.getAddress(CGF), RHS, Ignore);
4799  break;
4800 
4801  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4802  // __block variables need to have the rhs evaluated first, plus
4803  // this should improve codegen just a little.
4804  Value *Previous = nullptr;
4805  QualType SrcType = E->getRHS()->getType();
4806  // Check if LHS is a bitfield, if RHS contains an implicit cast expression
4807  // we want to extract that value and potentially (if the bitfield sanitizer
4808  // is enabled) use it to check for an implicit conversion.
4809  if (E->getLHS()->refersToBitField())
4810  RHS = CGF.EmitWithOriginalRHSBitfieldAssignment(E, &Previous, &SrcType);
4811  else
4812  RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4813 
4814  LHS = EmitCheckedLValue(E->getLHS(), CodeGenFunction::TCK_Store);
4815 
4816  // Store the value into the LHS. Bit-fields are handled specially
4817  // because the result is altered by the store, i.e., [C99 6.5.16p1]
4818  // 'An assignment expression has the value of the left operand after
4819  // the assignment...'.
4820  if (LHS.isBitField()) {
4821  CGF.EmitStoreThroughBitfieldLValue(RValue::get(RHS), LHS, &RHS);
4822  // If the expression contained an implicit conversion, make sure
4823  // to use the value before the scalar conversion.
4824  Value *Src = Previous ? Previous : RHS;
4825  QualType DstType = E->getLHS()->getType();
4826  CGF.EmitBitfieldConversionCheck(Src, SrcType, RHS, DstType,
4827  LHS.getBitFieldInfo(), E->getExprLoc());
4828  } else {
4829  CGF.EmitNullabilityCheck(LHS, RHS, E->getExprLoc());
4830  CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(RValue::get(RHS), LHS);
4831  }
4832  }
4833 
4834  // If the result is clearly ignored, return now.
4835  if (Ignore)
4836  return nullptr;
4837 
4838  // The result of an assignment in C is the assigned r-value.
4839  if (!CGF.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
4840  return RHS;
4841 
4842  // If the lvalue is non-volatile, return the computed value of the assignment.
4843  if (!LHS.isVolatileQualified())
4844  return RHS;
4845 
4846  // Otherwise, reload the value.
4847  return EmitLoadOfLValue(LHS, E->getExprLoc());
4848 }
4849 
4850 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinLAnd(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4851  // Perform vector logical and on comparisons with zero vectors.
4852  if (E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4853  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4854 
4855  Value *LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
4856  Value *RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4857  Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(LHS->getType());
4858  if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4859  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(
4860  CGF, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts()));
4861  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4862  RHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4863  } else {
4864  LHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
4865  RHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
4866  }
4867  Value *And = Builder.CreateAnd(LHS, RHS);
4868  return Builder.CreateSExt(And, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
4869  }
4870 
4871  bool InstrumentRegions = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasProfileClangInstr();
4872  llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
4873 
4874  // If we have 0 && RHS, see if we can elide RHS, if so, just return 0.
4875  // If we have 1 && X, just emit X without inserting the control flow.
4876  bool LHSCondVal;
4877  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSCondVal)) {
4878  if (LHSCondVal) { // If we have 1 && X, just emit X.
4879  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4880 
4881  // If the top of the logical operator nest, reset the MCDC temp to 0.
4882  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
4883  CGF.maybeResetMCDCCondBitmap(E);
4884 
4885  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.push_back(E);
4886 
4887  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4888 
4889  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch to a
4890  // block that increments the RHS counter needed to track branch condition
4891  // coverage. In this case, use "FBlock" as both the final "TrueBlock" and
4892  // "FalseBlock" after the increment is done.
4893  if (InstrumentRegions &&
4894  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
4895  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCCondBitmap(E->getRHS(), RHSCond);
4896  llvm::BasicBlock *FBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.end");
4897  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhscnt");
4898  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt, FBlock);
4899  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
4900  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
4901  CGF.EmitBranch(FBlock);
4902  CGF.EmitBlock(FBlock);
4903  }
4904 
4905  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.pop_back();
4906  // If the top of the logical operator nest, update the MCDC bitmap.
4907  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
4908  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCTestVectorBitmap(E);
4909 
4910  // ZExt result to int or bool.
4911  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(RHSCond, ResTy, "land.ext");
4912  }
4913 
4914  // 0 && RHS: If it is safe, just elide the RHS, and return 0/false.
4915  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(E->getRHS()))
4916  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(ResTy);
4917  }
4918 
4919  // If the top of the logical operator nest, reset the MCDC temp to 0.
4920  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
4921  CGF.maybeResetMCDCCondBitmap(E);
4922 
4923  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.push_back(E);
4924 
4925  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.end");
4926  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhs");
4927 
4928  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
4929 
4930  // Branch on the LHS first. If it is false, go to the failure (cont) block.
4931  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getLHS(), RHSBlock, ContBlock,
4932  CGF.getProfileCount(E->getRHS()));
4933 
4934  // Any edges into the ContBlock are now from an (indeterminate number of)
4935  // edges from this first condition. All of these values will be false. Start
4936  // setting up the PHI node in the Cont Block for this.
4937  llvm::PHINode *PN = llvm::PHINode::Create(llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), 2,
4938  "", ContBlock);
4939  for (llvm::pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(ContBlock), PE = pred_end(ContBlock);
4940  PI != PE; ++PI)
4941  PN->addIncoming(llvm::ConstantInt::getFalse(VMContext), *PI);
4942 
4943  eval.begin(CGF);
4944  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
4945  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4946  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
4947  eval.end(CGF);
4948 
4949  // Reaquire the RHS block, as there may be subblocks inserted.
4950  RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
4951 
4952  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch on the
4953  // RHS to a block that increments the RHS true counter needed to track branch
4954  // condition coverage.
4955  if (InstrumentRegions &&
4956  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
4957  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCCondBitmap(E->getRHS(), RHSCond);
4958  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("land.rhscnt");
4959  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt, ContBlock);
4960  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
4961  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
4962  CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
4963  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt);
4964  }
4965 
4966  // Emit an unconditional branch from this block to ContBlock.
4967  {
4968  // There is no need to emit line number for unconditional branch.
4969  auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateEmpty(CGF);
4970  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
4971  }
4972  // Insert an entry into the phi node for the edge with the value of RHSCond.
4973  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlock);
4974 
4975  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.pop_back();
4976  // If the top of the logical operator nest, update the MCDC bitmap.
4977  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
4978  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCTestVectorBitmap(E);
4979 
4980  // Artificial location to preserve the scope information
4981  {
4982  auto NL = ApplyDebugLocation::CreateArtificial(CGF);
4983  PN->setDebugLoc(Builder.getCurrentDebugLocation());
4984  }
4985 
4986  // ZExt result to int.
4987  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(PN, ResTy, "land.ext");
4988 }
4989 
4990 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinLOr(const BinaryOperator *E) {
4991  // Perform vector logical or on comparisons with zero vectors.
4992  if (E->getType()->isVectorType()) {
4993  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
4994 
4995  Value *LHS = Visit(E->getLHS());
4996  Value *RHS = Visit(E->getRHS());
4997  Value *Zero = llvm::ConstantAggregateZero::get(LHS->getType());
4998  if (LHS->getType()->isFPOrFPVectorTy()) {
4999  CodeGenFunction::CGFPOptionsRAII FPOptsRAII(
5000  CGF, E->getFPFeaturesInEffect(CGF.getLangOpts()));
5001  LHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
5002  RHS = Builder.CreateFCmp(llvm::CmpInst::FCMP_UNE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
5003  } else {
5004  LHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, LHS, Zero, "cmp");
5005  RHS = Builder.CreateICmp(llvm::CmpInst::ICMP_NE, RHS, Zero, "cmp");
5006  }
5007  Value *Or = Builder.CreateOr(LHS, RHS);
5008  return Builder.CreateSExt(Or, ConvertType(E->getType()), "sext");
5009  }
5010 
5011  bool InstrumentRegions = CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().hasProfileClangInstr();
5012  llvm::Type *ResTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
5013 
5014  // If we have 1 || RHS, see if we can elide RHS, if so, just return 1.
5015  // If we have 0 || X, just emit X without inserting the control flow.
5016  bool LHSCondVal;
5017  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(E->getLHS(), LHSCondVal)) {
5018  if (!LHSCondVal) { // If we have 0 || X, just emit X.
5019  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5020 
5021  // If the top of the logical operator nest, reset the MCDC temp to 0.
5022  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5023  CGF.maybeResetMCDCCondBitmap(E);
5024 
5025  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.push_back(E);
5026 
5027  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
5028 
5029  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch to a
5030  // block that increments the RHS counter need to track branch condition
5031  // coverage. In this case, use "FBlock" as both the final "TrueBlock" and
5032  // "FalseBlock" after the increment is done.
5033  if (InstrumentRegions &&
5034  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
5035  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCCondBitmap(E->getRHS(), RHSCond);
5036  llvm::BasicBlock *FBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.end");
5037  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhscnt");
5038  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, FBlock, RHSBlockCnt);
5039  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
5040  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
5041  CGF.EmitBranch(FBlock);
5042  CGF.EmitBlock(FBlock);
5043  }
5044 
5045  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.pop_back();
5046  // If the top of the logical operator nest, update the MCDC bitmap.
5047  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5048  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCTestVectorBitmap(E);
5049 
5050  // ZExt result to int or bool.
5051  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(RHSCond, ResTy, "lor.ext");
5052  }
5053 
5054  // 1 || RHS: If it is safe, just elide the RHS, and return 1/true.
5055  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(E->getRHS()))
5056  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(ResTy, 1);
5057  }
5058 
5059  // If the top of the logical operator nest, reset the MCDC temp to 0.
5060  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5061  CGF.maybeResetMCDCCondBitmap(E);
5062 
5063  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.push_back(E);
5064 
5065  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.end");
5066  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhs");
5067 
5068  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
5069 
5070  // Branch on the LHS first. If it is true, go to the success (cont) block.
5071  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(E->getLHS(), ContBlock, RHSBlock,
5072  CGF.getCurrentProfileCount() -
5073  CGF.getProfileCount(E->getRHS()));
5074 
5075  // Any edges into the ContBlock are now from an (indeterminate number of)
5076  // edges from this first condition. All of these values will be true. Start
5077  // setting up the PHI node in the Cont Block for this.
5078  llvm::PHINode *PN = llvm::PHINode::Create(llvm::Type::getInt1Ty(VMContext), 2,
5079  "", ContBlock);
5080  for (llvm::pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(ContBlock), PE = pred_end(ContBlock);
5081  PI != PE; ++PI)
5082  PN->addIncoming(llvm::ConstantInt::getTrue(VMContext), *PI);
5083 
5084  eval.begin(CGF);
5085 
5086  // Emit the RHS condition as a bool value.
5087  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
5088  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5089  Value *RHSCond = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(E->getRHS());
5090 
5091  eval.end(CGF);
5092 
5093  // Reaquire the RHS block, as there may be subblocks inserted.
5094  RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5095 
5096  // If we're generating for profiling or coverage, generate a branch on the
5097  // RHS to a block that increments the RHS true counter needed to track branch
5098  // condition coverage.
5099  if (InstrumentRegions &&
5100  CodeGenFunction::isInstrumentedCondition(E->getRHS())) {
5101  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCCondBitmap(E->getRHS(), RHSCond);
5102  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlockCnt = CGF.createBasicBlock("lor.rhscnt");
5103  Builder.CreateCondBr(RHSCond, ContBlock, RHSBlockCnt);
5104  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlockCnt);
5105  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E->getRHS());
5106  CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
5107  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlockCnt);
5108  }
5109 
5110  // Emit an unconditional branch from this block to ContBlock. Insert an entry
5111  // into the phi node for the edge with the value of RHSCond.
5112  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
5113  PN->addIncoming(RHSCond, RHSBlock);
5114 
5115  CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.pop_back();
5116  // If the top of the logical operator nest, update the MCDC bitmap.
5117  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5118  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCTestVectorBitmap(E);
5119 
5120  // ZExt result to int.
5121  return Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(PN, ResTy, "lor.ext");
5122 }
5123 
5124 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitBinComma(const BinaryOperator *E) {
5125  CGF.EmitIgnoredExpr(E->getLHS());
5126  CGF.EnsureInsertPoint();
5127  return Visit(E->getRHS());
5128 }

5130 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5131 // Other Operators
5132 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5133 
5134 /// isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally - Return true if the specified
5135 /// expression is cheap enough and side-effect-free enough to evaluate
5136 /// unconditionally instead of conditionally. This is used to convert control
5137 /// flow into selects in some cases.
5138 static bool isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(const Expr *E,
5139  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
5140  // Anything that is an integer or floating point constant is fine.
5141  return E->IgnoreParens()->isEvaluatable(CGF.getContext());
5142 
5143  // Even non-volatile automatic variables can't be evaluated unconditionally.
5144  // Referencing a thread_local may cause non-trivial initialization work to
5145  // occur. If we're inside a lambda and one of the variables is from the scope
5146  // outside the lambda, that function may have returned already. Reading its
5147  // locals is a bad idea. Also, these reads may introduce races there didn't
5148  // exist in the source-level program.
5149 }
5150 
5151 
5152 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::
5153 VisitAbstractConditionalOperator(const AbstractConditionalOperator *E) {
5154  TestAndClearIgnoreResultAssign();
5155 
5156  // Bind the common expression if necessary.
5157  CodeGenFunction::OpaqueValueMapping binding(CGF, E);
5158 
5159  Expr *condExpr = E->getCond();
5160  Expr *lhsExpr = E->getTrueExpr();
5161  Expr *rhsExpr = E->getFalseExpr();
5162 
5163  // If the condition constant folds and can be elided, try to avoid emitting
5164  // the condition and the dead arm.
5165  bool CondExprBool;
5166  if (CGF.ConstantFoldsToSimpleInteger(condExpr, CondExprBool)) {
5167  Expr *live = lhsExpr, *dead = rhsExpr;
5168  if (!CondExprBool) std::swap(live, dead);
5169 
5170  // If the dead side doesn't have labels we need, just emit the Live part.
5171  if (!CGF.ContainsLabel(dead)) {
5172  if (CondExprBool) {
5173  if (llvm::EnableSingleByteCoverage) {
5174  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(lhsExpr);
5175  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(rhsExpr);
5176  }
5177  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5178  }
5179  Value *Result = Visit(live);
5180 
5181  // If the live part is a throw expression, it acts like it has a void
5182  // type, so evaluating it returns a null Value*. However, a conditional
5183  // with non-void type must return a non-null Value*.
5184  if (!Result && !E->getType()->isVoidType())
5185  Result = llvm::UndefValue::get(CGF.ConvertType(E->getType()));
5186 
5187  return Result;
5188  }
5189  }
5190 
5191  // OpenCL: If the condition is a vector, we can treat this condition like
5192  // the select function.
5193  if ((CGF.getLangOpts().OpenCL && condExpr->getType()->isVectorType()) ||
5194  condExpr->getType()->isExtVectorType()) {
5195  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5196 
5197  llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(condExpr);
5198  llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
5199  llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
5200 
5201  llvm::Type *condType = ConvertType(condExpr->getType());
5202  auto *vecTy = cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(condType);
5203 
5204  unsigned numElem = vecTy->getNumElements();
5205  llvm::Type *elemType = vecTy->getElementType();
5206 
5207  llvm::Value *zeroVec = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(vecTy);
5208  llvm::Value *TestMSB = Builder.CreateICmpSLT(CondV, zeroVec);
5209  llvm::Value *tmp = Builder.CreateSExt(
5210  TestMSB, llvm::FixedVectorType::get(elemType, numElem), "sext");
5211  llvm::Value *tmp2 = Builder.CreateNot(tmp);
5212 
5213  // Cast float to int to perform ANDs if necessary.
5214  llvm::Value *RHSTmp = RHS;
5215  llvm::Value *LHSTmp = LHS;
5216  bool wasCast = false;
5217  llvm::VectorType *rhsVTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(RHS->getType());
5218  if (rhsVTy->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy()) {
5219  RHSTmp = Builder.CreateBitCast(RHS, tmp2->getType());
5220  LHSTmp = Builder.CreateBitCast(LHS, tmp->getType());
5221  wasCast = true;
5222  }
5223 
5224  llvm::Value *tmp3 = Builder.CreateAnd(RHSTmp, tmp2);
5225  llvm::Value *tmp4 = Builder.CreateAnd(LHSTmp, tmp);
5226  llvm::Value *tmp5 = Builder.CreateOr(tmp3, tmp4, "cond");
5227  if (wasCast)
5228  tmp5 = Builder.CreateBitCast(tmp5, RHS->getType());
5229 
5230  return tmp5;
5231  }
5232 
5233  if (condExpr->getType()->isVectorType() ||
5234  condExpr->getType()->isSveVLSBuiltinType()) {
5235  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5236 
5237  llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(condExpr);
5238  llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
5239  llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
5240 
5241  llvm::Type *CondType = ConvertType(condExpr->getType());
5242  auto *VecTy = cast<llvm::VectorType>(CondType);
5243  llvm::Value *ZeroVec = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(VecTy);
5244 
5245  CondV = Builder.CreateICmpNE(CondV, ZeroVec, "vector_cond");
5246  return Builder.CreateSelect(CondV, LHS, RHS, "vector_select");
5247  }
5248 
5249  // If this is a really simple expression (like x ? 4 : 5), emit this as a
5250  // select instead of as control flow. We can only do this if it is cheap and
5251  // safe to evaluate the LHS and RHS unconditionally.
5252  if (isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(lhsExpr, CGF) &&
5253  isCheapEnoughToEvaluateUnconditionally(rhsExpr, CGF)) {
5254  llvm::Value *CondV = CGF.EvaluateExprAsBool(condExpr);
5255  llvm::Value *StepV = Builder.CreateZExtOrBitCast(CondV, CGF.Int64Ty);
5256 
5257  if (llvm::EnableSingleByteCoverage) {
5258  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(lhsExpr);
5259  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(rhsExpr);
5260  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5261  } else
5262  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E, StepV);
5263 
5264  llvm::Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
5265  llvm::Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
5266  if (!LHS) {
5267  // If the conditional has void type, make sure we return a null Value*.
5268  assert(!RHS && "LHS and RHS types must match");
5269  return nullptr;
5270  }
5271  return Builder.CreateSelect(CondV, LHS, RHS, "cond");
5272  }
5273 
5274  // If the top of the logical operator nest, reset the MCDC temp to 0.
5275  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5276  CGF.maybeResetMCDCCondBitmap(condExpr);
5277 
5278  llvm::BasicBlock *LHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.true");
5279  llvm::BasicBlock *RHSBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.false");
5280  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("cond.end");
5281 
5282  CodeGenFunction::ConditionalEvaluation eval(CGF);
5283  CGF.EmitBranchOnBoolExpr(condExpr, LHSBlock, RHSBlock,
5284  CGF.getProfileCount(lhsExpr));
5285 
5286  CGF.EmitBlock(LHSBlock);
5287 
5288  // If the top of the logical operator nest, update the MCDC bitmap for the
5289  // ConditionalOperator prior to visiting its LHS and RHS blocks, since they
5290  // may also contain a boolean expression.
5291  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5292  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCTestVectorBitmap(condExpr);
5293 
5294  if (llvm::EnableSingleByteCoverage)
5295  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(lhsExpr);
5296  else
5297  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5298 
5299  eval.begin(CGF);
5300  Value *LHS = Visit(lhsExpr);
5301  eval.end(CGF);
5302 
5303  LHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5304  Builder.CreateBr(ContBlock);
5305 
5306  CGF.EmitBlock(RHSBlock);
5307 
5308  // If the top of the logical operator nest, update the MCDC bitmap for the
5309  // ConditionalOperator prior to visiting its LHS and RHS blocks, since they
5310  // may also contain a boolean expression.
5311  if (CGF.MCDCLogOpStack.empty())
5312  CGF.maybeUpdateMCDCTestVectorBitmap(condExpr);
5313 
5314  if (llvm::EnableSingleByteCoverage)
5315  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(rhsExpr);
5316 
5317  eval.begin(CGF);
5318  Value *RHS = Visit(rhsExpr);
5319  eval.end(CGF);
5320 
5321  RHSBlock = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
5322  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
5323 
5324  // If the LHS or RHS is a throw expression, it will be legitimately null.
5325  if (!LHS)
5326  return RHS;
5327  if (!RHS)
5328  return LHS;
5329 
5330  // Create a PHI node for the real part.
5331  llvm::PHINode *PN = Builder.CreatePHI(LHS->getType(), 2, "cond");
5332  PN->addIncoming(LHS, LHSBlock);
5333  PN->addIncoming(RHS, RHSBlock);
5334 
5335  // When single byte coverage mode is enabled, add a counter to continuation
5336  // block.
5337  if (llvm::EnableSingleByteCoverage)
5338  CGF.incrementProfileCounter(E);
5339 
5340  return PN;
5341 }

5344  return Visit(E->getChosenSubExpr());
5345 }

5347 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitVAArgExpr(VAArgExpr *VE) {
5348  QualType Ty = VE->getType();
5349 
5350  if (Ty->isVariablyModifiedType())
5351  CGF.EmitVariablyModifiedType(Ty);
5352 
5353  Address ArgValue = Address::invalid();
5354  Address ArgPtr = CGF.EmitVAArg(VE, ArgValue);
5355 
5356  llvm::Type *ArgTy = ConvertType(VE->getType());
5357 
5358  // If EmitVAArg fails, emit an error.
5359  if (!ArgPtr.isValid()) {
5360  CGF.ErrorUnsupported(VE, "va_arg expression");
5361  return llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgTy);
5362  }
5363 
5364  // FIXME Volatility.
5365  llvm::Value *Val = Builder.CreateLoad(ArgPtr);
5366 
5367  // If EmitVAArg promoted the type, we must truncate it.
5368  if (ArgTy != Val->getType()) {
5369  if (ArgTy->isPointerTy() && !Val->getType()->isPointerTy())
5370  Val = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Val, ArgTy);
5371  else
5372  Val = Builder.CreateTrunc(Val, ArgTy);
5373  }
5374 
5375  return Val;
5376 }

5382 // Convert a vec3 to vec4, or vice versa.
5383 static Value *ConvertVec3AndVec4(CGBuilderTy &Builder, CodeGenFunction &CGF,
5384  Value *Src, unsigned NumElementsDst) {
5385  static constexpr int Mask[] = {0, 1, 2, -1};
5386  return Builder.CreateShuffleVector(Src, llvm::ArrayRef(Mask, NumElementsDst));
5387 }
5388 
5389 // Create cast instructions for converting LLVM value \p Src to LLVM type \p
5390 // DstTy. \p Src has the same size as \p DstTy. Both are single value types
5391 // but could be scalar or vectors of different lengths, and either can be
5392 // pointer.
5393 // There are 4 cases:
5394 // 1. non-pointer -> non-pointer : needs 1 bitcast
5395 // 2. pointer -> pointer : needs 1 bitcast or addrspacecast
5396 // 3. pointer -> non-pointer
5397 // a) pointer -> intptr_t : needs 1 ptrtoint
5398 // b) pointer -> non-intptr_t : needs 1 ptrtoint then 1 bitcast
5399 // 4. non-pointer -> pointer
5400 // a) intptr_t -> pointer : needs 1 inttoptr
5401 // b) non-intptr_t -> pointer : needs 1 bitcast then 1 inttoptr
5402 // Note: for cases 3b and 4b two casts are required since LLVM casts do not
5403 // allow casting directly between pointer types and non-integer non-pointer
5404 // types.
5405 static Value *createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(CGBuilderTy &Builder,
5406  const llvm::DataLayout &DL,
5407  Value *Src, llvm::Type *DstTy,
5408  StringRef Name = "") {
5409  auto SrcTy = Src->getType();
5410 
5411  // Case 1.
5412  if (!SrcTy->isPointerTy() && !DstTy->isPointerTy())
5413  return Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
5414 
5415  // Case 2.
5416  if (SrcTy->isPointerTy() && DstTy->isPointerTy())
5417  return Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
5418 
5419  // Case 3.
5420  if (SrcTy->isPointerTy() && !DstTy->isPointerTy()) {
5421  // Case 3b.
5422  if (!DstTy->isIntegerTy())
5423  Src = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Src, DL.getIntPtrType(SrcTy));
5424  // Cases 3a and 3b.
5425  return Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(Src, DstTy, Name);
5426  }
5427 
5428  // Case 4b.
5429  if (!SrcTy->isIntegerTy())
5430  Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, DL.getIntPtrType(DstTy));
5431  // Cases 4a and 4b.
5432  return Builder.CreateIntToPtr(Src, DstTy, Name);
5433 }
5434 
5435 Value *ScalarExprEmitter::VisitAsTypeExpr(AsTypeExpr *E) {
5436  Value *Src = CGF.EmitScalarExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
5437  llvm::Type *DstTy = ConvertType(E->getType());
5438 
5439  llvm::Type *SrcTy = Src->getType();
5440  unsigned NumElementsSrc =
5441  isa<llvm::VectorType>(SrcTy)
5442  ? cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(SrcTy)->getNumElements()
5443  : 0;
5444  unsigned NumElementsDst =
5445  isa<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)
5446  ? cast<llvm::FixedVectorType>(DstTy)->getNumElements()
5447  : 0;
5448 
5449  // Use bit vector expansion for ext_vector_type boolean vectors.
5450  if (E->getType()->isExtVectorBoolType())
5451  return CGF.emitBoolVecConversion(Src, NumElementsDst, "astype");
5452 
5453  // Going from vec3 to non-vec3 is a special case and requires a shuffle
5454  // vector to get a vec4, then a bitcast if the target type is different.
5455  if (NumElementsSrc == 3 && NumElementsDst != 3) {
5456  Src = ConvertVec3AndVec4(Builder, CGF, Src, 4);
5457  Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(), Src,
5458  DstTy);
5459 
5460  Src->setName("astype");
5461  return Src;
5462  }
5463 
5464  // Going from non-vec3 to vec3 is a special case and requires a bitcast
5465  // to vec4 if the original type is not vec4, then a shuffle vector to
5466  // get a vec3.
5467  if (NumElementsSrc != 3 && NumElementsDst == 3) {
5468  auto *Vec4Ty = llvm::FixedVectorType::get(
5469  cast<llvm::VectorType>(DstTy)->getElementType(), 4);
5470  Src = createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(), Src,
5471  Vec4Ty);
5472 
5473  Src = ConvertVec3AndVec4(Builder, CGF, Src, 3);
5474  Src->setName("astype");
5475  return Src;
5476  }
5477 
5478  return createCastsForTypeOfSameSize(Builder, CGF.CGM.getDataLayout(),
5479  Src, DstTy, "astype");
5480 }

5539 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitObjCIsaExpr(const ObjCIsaExpr *E) {
5540  // object->isa or (*object).isa
5541  // Generate code as for: *(Class*)object
5542 
5543  Expr *BaseExpr = E->getBase();
5544  Address Addr = Address::invalid();
5545  if (BaseExpr->isPRValue()) {
5546  llvm::Type *BaseTy =
5547  ConvertTypeForMem(BaseExpr->getType()->getPointeeType());
5548  Addr = Address(EmitScalarExpr(BaseExpr), BaseTy, getPointerAlign());
5549  } else {
5550  Addr = EmitLValue(BaseExpr).getAddress(*this);
5551  }
5552

5554  Addr = Addr.withElementType(ConvertType(E->getType()));
5555  return MakeAddrLValue(Addr, E->getType());

5559 LValue CodeGenFunction::EmitCompoundAssignmentLValue(
5560  const CompoundAssignOperator *E) {
5561  ScalarExprEmitter Scalar(*this);
5562  Value *Result = nullptr;
5563  switch (E->getOpcode()) {
5564 #define COMPOUND_OP(Op) \
5565  case BO_##Op##Assign: \
5566  return Scalar.EmitCompoundAssignLValue(E, &ScalarExprEmitter::Emit##Op, \
5567  Result)
5568  COMPOUND_OP(Mul);
5569  COMPOUND_OP(Div);
5570  COMPOUND_OP(Rem);
5571  COMPOUND_OP(Add);
5572  COMPOUND_OP(Sub);
5573  COMPOUND_OP(Shl);
5574  COMPOUND_OP(Shr);
5575  COMPOUND_OP(And);
5576  COMPOUND_OP(Xor);
5577  COMPOUND_OP(Or);
5578 #undef COMPOUND_OP
5579 
5580  case BO_PtrMemD:
5581  case BO_PtrMemI:
5582  case BO_Mul:
5583  case BO_Div:
5584  case BO_Rem:
5585  case BO_Add:
5586  case BO_Sub:
5587  case BO_Shl:
5588  case BO_Shr:
5589  case BO_LT:
5590  case BO_GT:
5591  case BO_LE:
5592  case BO_GE:
5593  case BO_EQ:
5594  case BO_NE:
5595  case BO_Cmp:
5596  case BO_And:
5597  case BO_Xor:
5598  case BO_Or:
5599  case BO_LAnd:
5600  case BO_LOr:
5601  case BO_Assign:
5602  case BO_Comma:
5603  llvm_unreachable("Not valid compound assignment operators");
5604  }
5605 
5606  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled compound assignment operator");
5607 }

5609 struct GEPOffsetAndOverflow {
5610  // The total (signed) byte offset for the GEP.
5611  llvm::Value *TotalOffset;
5612  // The offset overflow flag - true if the total offset overflows.
5613  llvm::Value *OffsetOverflows;
5614 };
5615 
5616 /// Evaluate given GEPVal, which is either an inbounds GEP, or a constant,
5617 /// and compute the total offset it applies from it's base pointer BasePtr.
5618 /// Returns offset in bytes and a boolean flag whether an overflow happened
5619 /// during evaluation.
5620 static GEPOffsetAndOverflow EmitGEPOffsetInBytes(Value *BasePtr, Value *GEPVal,
5621  llvm::LLVMContext &VMContext,
5622  CodeGenModule &CGM,
5623  CGBuilderTy &Builder) {
5624  const auto &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
5625 
5626  // The total (signed) byte offset for the GEP.
5627  llvm::Value *TotalOffset = nullptr;
5628 
5629  // Was the GEP already reduced to a constant?
5630  if (isa<llvm::Constant>(GEPVal)) {
5631  // Compute the offset by casting both pointers to integers and subtracting:
5632  // GEPVal = BasePtr + ptr(Offset) <--> Offset = int(GEPVal) - int(BasePtr)
5633  Value *BasePtr_int =
5634  Builder.CreatePtrToInt(BasePtr, DL.getIntPtrType(BasePtr->getType()));
5635  Value *GEPVal_int =
5636  Builder.CreatePtrToInt(GEPVal, DL.getIntPtrType(GEPVal->getType()));
5637  TotalOffset = Builder.CreateSub(GEPVal_int, BasePtr_int);
5638  return {TotalOffset, /*OffsetOverflows=*/Builder.getFalse()};
5639  }
5640 
5641  auto *GEP = cast<llvm::GEPOperator>(GEPVal);
5642  assert(GEP->getPointerOperand() == BasePtr &&
5643  "BasePtr must be the base of the GEP.");
5644  assert(GEP->isInBounds() && "Expected inbounds GEP");
5645 
5646  auto *IntPtrTy = DL.getIntPtrType(GEP->getPointerOperandType());
5647 
5648  // Grab references to the signed add/mul overflow intrinsics for intptr_t.
5649  auto *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
5650  auto *SAddIntrinsic =
5651  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow, IntPtrTy);
5652  auto *SMulIntrinsic =
5653  CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow, IntPtrTy);
5654 
5655  // The offset overflow flag - true if the total offset overflows.
5656  llvm::Value *OffsetOverflows = Builder.getFalse();
5657 
5658  /// Return the result of the given binary operation.
5659  auto eval = [&](BinaryOperator::Opcode Opcode, llvm::Value *LHS,
5660  llvm::Value *RHS) -> llvm::Value * {
5661  assert((Opcode == BO_Add || Opcode == BO_Mul) && "Can't eval binop");
5662 
5663  // If the operands are constants, return a constant result.
5664  if (auto *LHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(LHS)) {
5665  if (auto *RHSCI = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(RHS)) {
5666  llvm::APInt N;
5667  bool HasOverflow = mayHaveIntegerOverflow(LHSCI, RHSCI, Opcode,
5668  /*Signed=*/true, N);
5669  if (HasOverflow)
5670  OffsetOverflows = Builder.getTrue();
5671  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(VMContext, N);
5672  }
5673  }
5674 
5675  // Otherwise, compute the result with checked arithmetic.
5676  auto *ResultAndOverflow = Builder.CreateCall(
5677  (Opcode == BO_Add) ? SAddIntrinsic : SMulIntrinsic, {LHS, RHS});
5678  OffsetOverflows = Builder.CreateOr(
5679  Builder.CreateExtractValue(ResultAndOverflow, 1), OffsetOverflows);
5680  return Builder.CreateExtractValue(ResultAndOverflow, 0);
5681  };
5682 
5683  // Determine the total byte offset by looking at each GEP operand.
5684  for (auto GTI = llvm::gep_type_begin(GEP), GTE = llvm::gep_type_end(GEP);
5685  GTI != GTE; ++GTI) {
5686  llvm::Value *LocalOffset;
5687  auto *Index = GTI.getOperand();
5688  // Compute the local offset contributed by this indexing step:
5689  if (auto *STy = GTI.getStructTypeOrNull()) {
5690  // For struct indexing, the local offset is the byte position of the
5691  // specified field.
5692  unsigned FieldNo = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Index)->getZExtValue();
5693  LocalOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5694  IntPtrTy, DL.getStructLayout(STy)->getElementOffset(FieldNo));
5695  } else {
5696  // Otherwise this is array-like indexing. The local offset is the index
5697  // multiplied by the element size.
5698  auto *ElementSize =
5699  llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntPtrTy, GTI.getSequentialElementStride(DL));
5700  auto *IndexS = Builder.CreateIntCast(Index, IntPtrTy, /*isSigned=*/true);
5701  LocalOffset = eval(BO_Mul, ElementSize, IndexS);
5702  }
5703 
5704  // If this is the first offset, set it as the total offset. Otherwise, add
5705  // the local offset into the running total.
5706  if (!TotalOffset || TotalOffset == Zero)
5707  TotalOffset = LocalOffset;
5708  else
5709  TotalOffset = eval(BO_Add, TotalOffset, LocalOffset);
5710  }
5711 
5712  return {TotalOffset, OffsetOverflows};
5713 }
5714 
5715 Value *
5716 CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(llvm::Type *ElemTy, Value *Ptr,
5717  ArrayRef<Value *> IdxList,
5718  bool SignedIndices, bool IsSubtraction,
5719  SourceLocation Loc, const Twine &Name) {
5720  llvm::Type *PtrTy = Ptr->getType();
5721  Value *GEPVal = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(ElemTy, Ptr, IdxList, Name);
5722 
5723  // If the pointer overflow sanitizer isn't enabled, do nothing.
5724  if (!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow))
5725  return GEPVal;
5726 
5727  // Perform nullptr-and-offset check unless the nullptr is defined.
5728  bool PerformNullCheck = !NullPointerIsDefined(
5729  Builder.GetInsertBlock()->getParent(), PtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace());
5730  // Check for overflows unless the GEP got constant-folded,
5731  // and only in the default address space
5732  bool PerformOverflowCheck =
5733  !isa<llvm::Constant>(GEPVal) && PtrTy->getPointerAddressSpace() == 0;
5734 
5735  if (!(PerformNullCheck || PerformOverflowCheck))
5736  return GEPVal;
5737 
5738  const auto &DL = CGM.getDataLayout();
5739 
5740  SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
5741  llvm::Type *IntPtrTy = DL.getIntPtrType(PtrTy);
5742 
5743  GEPOffsetAndOverflow EvaluatedGEP =
5744  EmitGEPOffsetInBytes(Ptr, GEPVal, getLLVMContext(), CGM, Builder);
5745 
5746  assert((!isa<llvm::Constant>(EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset) ||
5747  EvaluatedGEP.OffsetOverflows == Builder.getFalse()) &&
5748  "If the offset got constant-folded, we don't expect that there was an "
5749  "overflow.");
5750 
5751  auto *Zero = llvm::ConstantInt::getNullValue(IntPtrTy);
5752 
5753  // Common case: if the total offset is zero, and we are using C++ semantics,
5754  // where nullptr+0 is defined, don't emit a check.
5755  if (EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset == Zero && CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5756  return GEPVal;
5757 
5758  // Now that we've computed the total offset, add it to the base pointer (with
5759  // wrapping semantics).
5760  auto *IntPtr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Ptr, IntPtrTy);
5761  auto *ComputedGEP = Builder.CreateAdd(IntPtr, EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset);
5762 
5763  llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<llvm::Value *, SanitizerMask>, 2> Checks;
5764 
5765  if (PerformNullCheck) {
5766  // In C++, if the base pointer evaluates to a null pointer value,
5767  // the only valid pointer this inbounds GEP can produce is also
5768  // a null pointer, so the offset must also evaluate to zero.
5769  // Likewise, if we have non-zero base pointer, we can not get null pointer
5770  // as a result, so the offset can not be -intptr_t(BasePtr).
5771  // In other words, both pointers are either null, or both are non-null,
5772  // or the behaviour is undefined.
5773  //
5774  // C, however, is more strict in this regard, and gives more
5775  // optimization opportunities: in C, additionally, nullptr+0 is undefined.
5776  // So both the input to the 'gep inbounds' AND the output must not be null.
5777  auto *BaseIsNotNullptr = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Ptr);
5778  auto *ResultIsNotNullptr = Builder.CreateIsNotNull(ComputedGEP);
5779  auto *Valid =
5780  CGM.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
5781  ? Builder.CreateICmpEQ(BaseIsNotNullptr, ResultIsNotNullptr)
5782  : Builder.CreateAnd(BaseIsNotNullptr, ResultIsNotNullptr);
5783  Checks.emplace_back(Valid, SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow);
5784  }
5785 
5786  if (PerformOverflowCheck) {
5787  // The GEP is valid if:
5788  // 1) The total offset doesn't overflow, and
5789  // 2) The sign of the difference between the computed address and the base
5790  // pointer matches the sign of the total offset.
5791  llvm::Value *ValidGEP;
5792  auto *NoOffsetOverflow = Builder.CreateNot(EvaluatedGEP.OffsetOverflows);
5793  if (SignedIndices) {
5794  // GEP is computed as `unsigned base + signed offset`, therefore:
5795  // * If offset was positive, then the computed pointer can not be
5796  // [unsigned] less than the base pointer, unless it overflowed.
5797  // * If offset was negative, then the computed pointer can not be
5798  // [unsigned] greater than the bas pointere, unless it overflowed.
5799  auto *PosOrZeroValid = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5800  auto *PosOrZeroOffset =
5801  Builder.CreateICmpSGE(EvaluatedGEP.TotalOffset, Zero);
5802  llvm::Value *NegValid = Builder.CreateICmpULT(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5803  ValidGEP =
5804  Builder.CreateSelect(PosOrZeroOffset, PosOrZeroValid, NegValid);
5805  } else if (!IsSubtraction) {
5806  // GEP is computed as `unsigned base + unsigned offset`, therefore the
5807  // computed pointer can not be [unsigned] less than base pointer,
5808  // unless there was an overflow.
5809  // Equivalent to `@llvm.uadd.with.overflow(%base, %offset)`.
5810  ValidGEP = Builder.CreateICmpUGE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5811  } else {
5812  // GEP is computed as `unsigned base - unsigned offset`, therefore the
5813  // computed pointer can not be [unsigned] greater than base pointer,
5814  // unless there was an overflow.
5815  // Equivalent to `@llvm.usub.with.overflow(%base, sub(0, %offset))`.
5816  ValidGEP = Builder.CreateICmpULE(ComputedGEP, IntPtr);
5817  }
5818  ValidGEP = Builder.CreateAnd(ValidGEP, NoOffsetOverflow);
5819  Checks.emplace_back(ValidGEP, SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow);
5820  }
5821 
5822  assert(!Checks.empty() && "Should have produced some checks.");
5823 
5824  llvm::Constant *StaticArgs[] = {EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc)};
5825  // Pass the computed GEP to the runtime to avoid emitting poisoned arguments.
5826  llvm::Value *DynamicArgs[] = {IntPtr, ComputedGEP};
5827  EmitCheck(Checks, SanitizerHandler::PointerOverflow, StaticArgs, DynamicArgs);
5828 
5829  return GEPVal;
5830 }
5831 
5832 Address CodeGenFunction::EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(
5833  Address Addr, ArrayRef<Value *> IdxList, llvm::Type *elementType,
5834  bool SignedIndices, bool IsSubtraction, SourceLocation Loc, CharUnits Align,
5835  const Twine &Name) {
5836  if (!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::PointerOverflow))
5837  return Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Addr, IdxList, elementType, Align, Name);
5838 
5839  return RawAddress(
5840  EmitCheckedInBoundsGEP(Addr.getElementType(), Addr.emitRawPointer(*this),
5841  IdxList, SignedIndices, IsSubtraction, Loc, Name),
5842  elementType, Align);
5843 }
